Name: bulbasaur
Summary: Bulbasaur is a Grass & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Bulbasaur's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 1,115. Bulbasaur evolves into Ivysaur.
About: Bulbasaur can be seen napping in bright sunlight. There is a seed on its back. By soaking up the sun's rays, the seed grows progressively larger.

Name: ivysaur
Summary: Ivysaur is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Bulbasaur. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Ivysaur's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 1,699. Ivysaur evolves into Venusaur.
About: There is a bud on this Pokémon's back. To support its weight, Ivysaur's legs and trunk grow thick and strong. If it starts spending more time lying in the sunlight, it's a sign that the bud will bloom into a large flower soon.

Name: venusaur
Summary: Venusaur is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Ivysaur. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Venusaur's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Frenzy Plant and it has a Max CP of 2,720.
About: There is a large flower on Venusaur's back. The flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the emotions of people.

Name: charmander
Summary: Charmander is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Charmander's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 980. Charmander evolves into Charmeleon.
About: The flame that burns at the tip of its tail is an indication of its emotions. The flame wavers when Charmander is enjoying itself. If the Pokémon becomes enraged, the flame burns fiercely.

Name: charmeleon
Summary: Charmeleon is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Charmander. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Charmeleon's strongest moveset is Fire Fang & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,653. Charmeleon evolves into Charizard.
About: Charmeleon mercilessly destroys its foes using its sharp claws. If it encounters a strong foe, it turns aggressive. In this excited state, the flame at the tip of its tail flares with a bluish white color.

Name: charizard
Summary: Charizard is a Fire & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Charmeleon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Electric and Water moves. Charizard's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Blast Burn and it has a Max CP of 2,889.
About: Charizard flies around the sky in search of powerful opponents. It breathes fire of such great heat that it melts anything. However, it never turns its fiery breath on any opponent weaker than itself.

Name: squirtle
Summary: Squirtle is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Squirtle's strongest moveset is Bubble & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 946. Squirtle evolves into Wartortle.
About: Squirtle's shell is not merely used for protection. The shell's rounded shape and the grooves on its surface help minimize resistance in water, enabling this Pokémon to swim at high speeds.

Name: wartortle
Summary: Wartortle is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Squirtle. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Wartortle's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 1,488. Wartortle evolves into Blastoise.
About: Its tail is large and covered with a rich, thick fur. The tail becomes increasingly deeper in color as Wartortle ages. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this Pokémon's toughness as a battler.

Name: blastoise
Summary: Blastoise is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Wartortle. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Blastoise's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,466.
About: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.

Name: caterpie
Summary: Caterpie is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Caterpie's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 437. Caterpie evolves into Metapod.
About: Caterpie has a voracious appetite. It can devour leaves bigger than its body right before your eyes. From its antenna, this Pokémon releases a terrifically strong odor.

Name: metapod
Summary: Metapod is a Bug Pokémon which evolves from Caterpie. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Metapod's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 450. Metapod evolves into Butterfree.
About: The shell covering this Pokémon's body is as hard as an iron slab. Metapod does not move very much. It stays still because it is preparing its soft innards for evolution inside the hard shell.

Name: butterfree
Summary: Butterfree is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Metapod. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Butterfree's strongest moveset is Confusion & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,827.
About: Butterfree has a superior ability to search for delicious honey from flowers. It can even search out, extract, and carry honey from flowers that are blooming over six miles from its nest.

Name: weedle
Summary: Weedle is a Bug & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Weedle's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Return and it has a Max CP of 456. Weedle evolves into Kakuna.
About: Weedle has an extremely acute sense of smell. It is capable of distinguishing its favorite kinds of leaves from those it dislikes just by sniffing with its big red proboscis (nose).

Name: kakuna
Summary: Kakuna is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Weedle. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Kakuna's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Return and it has a Max CP of 432. Kakuna evolves into Beedrill.
About: Kakuna remains virtually immobile as it clings to a tree. However, on the inside, it is extremely busy as it prepares for its coming evolution. This is evident from how hot the shell becomes to the touch.

Name: beedrill
Summary: Beedrill is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Kakuna. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Beedrill's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,846.
About: Beedrill is extremely territorial. No one should ever approach its nest—this is for their own safety. If angered, they will attack in a furious swarm.

Name: pidgey
Summary: Pidgey is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Pidgey's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 680. Pidgey evolves into Pidgeotto.
About: Pidgey has an extremely sharp sense of direction. It is capable of unerringly returning home to its nest, however far it may be removed from its familiar surroundings.

Name: pidgeotto
Summary: Pidgeotto is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Pidgey. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Pidgeotto's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 1,194. Pidgeotto evolves into Pidgeot.
About: Pidgeotto claims a large area as its own territory. This Pokémon flies around, patrolling its living space. If its territory is violated, it shows no mercy in thoroughly punishing the foe with its sharp claws.

Name: pidgeot
Summary: Pidgeot is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Pidgeotto. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Pidgeot's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Hurricane and it has a Max CP of 2,129.
About: This Pokémon has a dazzling plumage of beautifully glossy feathers. Many Trainers are captivated by the striking beauty of the feathers on its head, compelling them to choose Pidgeot as their Pokémon.

Name: rattata
Summary: Rattata is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Rattata's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Hyper Fang and it has a Max CP of 734. Rattata evolves into Raticate.
About: Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly listens by moving its ears around. It is not picky about where it lives—it will make its nest anywhere.

Name: raticate
Summary: Raticate is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Rattata. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Raticate's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,730.
About: Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.

Name: spearow
Summary: Spearow is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Spearow's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 798. Spearow evolves into Fearow.
About: Spearow has a very loud cry that can be heard over half a mile away. If its high, keening cry is heard echoing all around, it is a sign that they are warning each other of danger.

Name: fearow
Summary: Fearow is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Spearow. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Fearow's strongest moveset is Peck & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 1,997.
About: Fearow is recognized by its long neck and elongated beak. They are conveniently shaped for catching prey in soil or water. It deftly moves its long and skinny beak to pluck prey.

Name: ekans
Summary: Ekans is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Ekans's strongest moveset is Acid & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 927. Ekans evolves into Arbok.
About: Ekans curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any direction with a glare from its upraised head.

Name: arbok
Summary: Arbok is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Ekans. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Arbok's strongest moveset is Acid & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 1,921.
About: This Pokémon is terrifically strong in order to constrict things with its body. It can even flatten steel oil drums. Once Arbok wraps its body around its foe, escaping its crushing embrace is impossible.

Name: pikachu
Summary: Pikachu is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Pikachu's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 938. Pikachu evolves into Raichu.
About: Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokémon mistook the intensity of its charge.

Name: raichu
Summary: Raichu is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Raichu's strongest moveset is Volt Switch & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 2,182.
About: If the electrical sacs become excessively charged, Raichu plants its tail in the ground and discharges. Scorched patches of ground will be found near this Pokémon's nest.

Name: sandshrew
Summary: Sandshrew is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Sandshrew's strongest moveset is Mud Shot & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,261. Sandshrew evolves into Sandslash.
About: Sandshrew's body is configured to absorb water without waste, enabling it to survive in an arid desert. This Pokémon curls up to protect itself from its enemies.

Name: sandslash
Summary: Sandslash is a Ground Pokémon which evolves from Sandshrew. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Sandslash's strongest moveset is Mud Shot & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,374.
About: Sandslash's body is covered by tough spikes, which are hardened sections of its hide. Once a year, the old spikes fall out, to be replaced with new spikes that grow out from beneath the old ones.

Name: nidoran♀
Summary: Nidoran♀ is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Nidoran♀'s strongest moveset is Poison Sting & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 816. Nidoran♀ evolves into Nidorina.
About: Nidoran♀ has barbs that secrete a powerful poison. They are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied Pokémon. When enraged, it releases a horrible toxin from its horn.

Name: nidorina
Summary: Nidorina is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Nidoran♀. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Nidorina's strongest moveset is Poison Sting & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,309. Nidorina evolves into Nidoqueen.
About: When Nidorina are with their friends or family, they keep their barbs tucked away to prevent hurting each other. This Pokémon appears to become nervous if separated from the others.

Name: nidoqueen
Summary: Nidoqueen is a Poison & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Nidorina. It is vulnerable to Water, Ground, Ice and Psychic moves. Nidoqueen's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,488.
About: Nidoqueen's body is encased in extremely hard scales. It is adept at sending foes flying with harsh tackles. This Pokémon is at its strongest when it is defending its young.

Name: nidoran♂
Summary: Nidoran♂ is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Nidoran♂'s strongest moveset is Poison Sting & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 860. Nidoran♂ evolves into Nidorino.
About: Nidoran♂ has developed muscles for moving its ears. Thanks to them, the ears can be freely moved in any direction. Even the slightest sound does not escape this Pokémon's notice.

Name: nidorino
Summary: Nidorino is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Nidoran♂. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Nidorino's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,393. Nidorino evolves into Nidoking.
About: Nidorino has a horn that is harder than a diamond. If it senses a hostile presence, all the barbs on its back bristle up at once, and it challenges the foe with all its might.

Name: nidoking
Summary: Nidoking is a Poison & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Nidorino. It is vulnerable to Water, Ground, Ice and Psychic moves. Nidoking's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,567.
About: Nidoking's thick tail packs enormously destructive power. With one swing, it can topple a metal transmission tower. Once this Pokémon goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.

Name: clefairy
Summary: Clefairy is a Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Cleffa. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Clefairy's strongest moveset is Pound & Moonblast and it has a Max CP of 1,155. Clefairy evolves into Clefable.
About: On every night of a full moon, groups of this Pokémon come out to play. When dawn arrives, the tired Clefairy return to their quiet mountain retreats and go to sleep nestled up against each other.

Name: clefable
Summary: Clefable is a Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Clefairy. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Clefable's strongest moveset is Charm & Meteor Mash and it has a Max CP of 2,437.
About: Clefable moves by skipping lightly as if it were flying using its wings. Its bouncy step lets it even walk on water. It is known to take strolls on lakes on quiet, moonlit nights.

Name: vulpix
Summary: Vulpix is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Vulpix's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 883. Vulpix evolves into Ninetales.
About: At the time of its birth, Vulpix has one white tail. The tail separates into six if this Pokémon receives plenty of love from its Trainer. The six tails become magnificently curled.

Name: ninetales
Summary: Ninetales is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Vulpix. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Ninetales's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 2,279.
About: Ninetales casts a sinister light from its bright red eyes to gain total control over its foe's mind. This Pokémon is said to live for a thousand years.

Name: jigglypuff
Summary: Jigglypuff is a Normal & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Igglybuff. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Jigglypuff's strongest moveset is Pound & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 724. Jigglypuff evolves into Wigglytuff.
About: Jigglypuff's vocal cords can freely adjust the wavelength of its voice. This Pokémon uses this ability to sing at precisely the right wavelength to make its foes most drowsy.

Name: wigglytuff
Summary: Wigglytuff is a Normal & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Jigglypuff. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Wigglytuff's strongest moveset is Pound & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,926.
About: Wigglytuff has large, saucerlike eyes. The surfaces of its eyes are always covered with a thin layer of tears. If any dust gets in this Pokémon's eyes, it is quickly washed away.

Name: zubat
Summary: Zubat is a Poison & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Psychic and Electric moves. Zubat's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 667. Zubat evolves into Golbat.
About: Zubat remains quietly unmoving in a dark spot during the bright daylight hours. It does so because prolonged exposure to the sun causes its body to become slightly burned.

Name: golbat
Summary: Golbat is a Poison & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Zubat. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Psychic and Electric moves. Golbat's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,976. Golbat evolves into Crobat.
About: Golbat loves to drink the blood of living things. It is particularly active in the pitch black of night. This Pokémon flits around in the night skies, seeking fresh blood.

Name: oddish
Summary: Oddish is a Grass & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Oddish's strongest moveset is Acid & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,228. Oddish evolves into Gloom.
About: During the daytime, Oddish buries itself in soil to absorb nutrients from the ground using its entire body. The more fertile the soil, the glossier its leaves become.

Name: gloom
Summary: Gloom is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Oddish. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Gloom's strongest moveset is Acid & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,681. Gloom evolves into Vileplume, Bellossom.
About: Gloom releases a foul fragrance from the pistil of its flower. When faced with danger, the stench worsens. If this Pokémon is feeling calm and secure, it does not release its usual stinky aroma.

Name: vileplume
Summary: Vileplume is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Gloom. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Vileplume's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,559.
About: Vileplume's toxic pollen triggers atrocious allergy attacks. That's why it is advisable never to approach any attractive flowers in a jungle, however pretty they may be.

Name: paras
Summary: Paras is a Bug & Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Rock, Bug and Ice moves. Paras's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Seed Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,018. Paras evolves into Parasect.
About: Night after night, they sneak into people's homes seeking food. A massive outbreak of them has become an issue of public concern.

Name: parasect
Summary: Parasect is a Bug & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Paras. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Rock, Bug and Ice moves. Parasect's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,859.
About: Parasect is known to infest large trees en masse and drain nutrients from the lower trunk and roots. When an infested tree dies, they move onto another tree all at once.

Name: venonat
Summary: Venonat is a Bug & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Venonat's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Signal Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,004. Venonat evolves into Venomoth.
About: It commands a nest of Rattata. Different nests don't get along, whipping up severe fights over feeding grounds.

Name: venomoth
Summary: Venomoth is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Venonat. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Venomoth's strongest moveset is Infestation & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 2,082.
About: Venomoth is nocturnal—it is a Pokémon that only becomes active at night. Its favorite prey are small insects that gather around streetlights, attracted by the light in the darkness.

Name: diglett
Summary: Diglett is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Diglett's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Return and it has a Max CP of 676. Diglett evolves into Dugtrio.
About: When you rub its cheeks, a sweet fragrance comes wafting out. However, you'll also get a light shock!

Name: dugtrio
Summary: Dugtrio is a Ground Pokémon which evolves from Diglett. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Dugtrio's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 1,567.
About: Dugtrio are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly.

Name: meowth
Summary: Meowth is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Meowth's strongest moveset is Scratch & Return and it has a Max CP of 748. Meowth evolves into Persian.
About: The skin on its back is as hard as steel. Predators go after its soft belly, so it clings to the ground desperately.

Name: persian
Summary: Persian is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Meowth. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Persian's strongest moveset is Scratch & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,689.
About: Persian has six bold whiskers that give it a look of toughness. The whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in the Pokémon's surrounding vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.

Name: psyduck
Summary: Psyduck is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Psyduck's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 1,106. Psyduck evolves into Golduck.
About: A long, long time ago, it lived in the desert. With its sharp claws fully extended, it can climb right up an iceberg without slipping.

Name: golduck
Summary: Golduck is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Psyduck. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Golduck's strongest moveset is Confusion & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,450.
About: The webbed flippers on its forelegs and hind legs and the streamlined body of Golduck give it frightening speed. This Pokémon is definitely much faster than even the most athletic swimmer.

Name: mankey
Summary: Mankey is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Mankey's strongest moveset is Karate Chop & Cross Chop and it has a Max CP of 1,164. Mankey evolves into Primeape.
About: They live together in a skulk, helping one another. Before eating their prey, they freeze it solid with their –58 degree Fahrenheit breath.

Name: primeape
Summary: Primeape is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Mankey. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Primeape's strongest moveset is Counter & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,288.
About: When Primeape becomes furious, its blood circulation is boosted. In turn, its muscles are made even stronger. However, it also becomes much less intelligent at the same time.

Name: growlithe
Summary: Growlithe is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Growlithe's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,243. Growlithe evolves into Arcanine.
About: Some said that deities visited mountains where Ninetales live, so in times long past, no one was allowed to go into those mountains.

Name: arcanine
Summary: Arcanine is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Growlithe. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Arcanine's strongest moveset is Fire Fang & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 3,029.
About: Arcanine is known for its high speed. It is said to be capable of running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within this Pokémon's body is its source of power.

Name: poliwag
Summary: Poliwag is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Poliwag's strongest moveset is Bubble & Return and it has a Max CP of 829. Poliwag evolves into Poliwhirl.
About: The need to dig through volcanic rock in the ground has made them more powerful than the Diglett of other regions.

Name: poliwhirl
Summary: Poliwhirl is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Poliwag. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Poliwhirl's strongest moveset is Bubble & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,419. Poliwhirl evolves into Poliwrath, Politoed.
About: The surface of Poliwhirl's body is always wet and slick with a slimy fluid. Because of this slippery covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.

Name: poliwrath
Summary: Poliwrath is a Water & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Poliwhirl. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying, Psychic, Electric and Grass moves. Poliwrath's strongest moveset is Bubble & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 2,586.
About: Its shining gold whiskers are advanced sensors that can detect vibrations from sounds several miles away.

Name: abra
Summary: Abra is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Abra's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,342. Abra evolves into Kadabra.
About: Abra sleeps for 18 hours a day. However, it can sense the presence of foes even while it is sleeping. In such a situation, this Pokémon immediately teleports to safety.

Name: kadabra
Summary: Kadabra is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Abra. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Kadabra's strongest moveset is Confusion & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,059. Kadabra evolves into Alakazam.
About: A royal house that flourished in the distant past brought it here from another region. Meowth is both selfish and prideful.

Name: alakazam
Summary: Alakazam is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Kadabra. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Alakazam's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 3,057.
About: Alakazam's brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This Pokémon holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.

Name: machop
Summary: Machop is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Machop's strongest moveset is Karate Chop & Cross Chop and it has a Max CP of 1,278. Machop evolves into Machoke.
About: Its round face is a symbol of wealth. Persian that have bigger, plumper faces are considered more beautiful.

Name: machoke
Summary: Machoke is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Machop. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Machoke's strongest moveset is Karate Chop & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 2,031. Machoke evolves into Machamp.
About: Machoke's thoroughly toned muscles possess the hardness of steel. This Pokémon has so much strength, it can easily hold aloft a sumo wrestler on just one finger.

Name: machamp
Summary: Machamp is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Machoke. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Machamp's strongest moveset is Counter & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 3,056.
About: Geodude compete against each other with headbutts. The iron sand on their heads will stick to whichever one has stronger magnetism.

Name: bellsprout
Summary: Bellsprout is a Grass & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Bellsprout's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 1,033. Bellsprout evolves into Weepinbell.
About: Bellsprout's thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack, however strong it may be. From its mouth, this Pokémon spits a corrosive fluid that melts even iron.

Name: weepinbell
Summary: Weepinbell is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Bellsprout. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Weepinbell's strongest moveset is Acid & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 1,611. Weepinbell evolves into Victreebel.
About: Graveler's entire body is tinged with electricity due to the stones it likes to eat. It's very quick-tempered.

Name: victreebel
Summary: Victreebel is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Weepinbell. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Victreebel's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,431.
About: Victreebel has a long vine that extends from its head. This vine is waved and flicked about as if it were an animal to attract prey. When an unsuspecting prey draws near, this Pokémon swallows it whole.

Name: tentacool
Summary: Tentacool is a Water & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Psychic and Electric moves. Tentacool's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,040. Tentacool evolves into Tentacruel.
About: It shoots large rocks that are charged with electricity. Tremendous electric shocks are flung out across the whole area of impact.

Name: tentacruel
Summary: Tentacruel is a Water & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Tentacool. It is vulnerable to Ground, Psychic and Electric moves. Tentacruel's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,422.
About: Tentacruel has large red orbs on its head. The orbs glow before lashing the vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast. This Pokémon's outburst creates rough waves around it.

Name: geodude
Summary: Geodude is a Rock & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Geodude's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 1,293. Geodude evolves into Graveler.
About: Brought to Alola to solve the garbage problem, Grimer seems to relish any and all kinds of trash.

Name: graveler
Summary: Graveler is a Rock & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Geodude. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Graveler's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 1,897. Graveler evolves into Golem.
About: Graveler grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This Pokémon eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis.

Name: golem
Summary: Golem is a Rock & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Graveler. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Golem's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,949.
About: What look like fangs and claws are actually crystallized poison that will afflict you at a mere touch, so don't get too close.

Name: ponyta
Summary: Ponyta is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Ponyta's strongest moveset is Ember & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 1,697. Ponyta evolves into Rapidash.
About: Ponyta is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. This Pokémon becomes stronger by stumbling and falling to keep up with its parent.

Name: rapidash
Summary: Rapidash is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Ponyta. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Rapidash's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 2,461.
About: It swings its long neck like a whip and smacks its opponents. This makes Exeggutor itself dizzy, too.

Name: slowpoke
Summary: Slowpoke is a Water & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ghost, Dark, Electric, Grass and Bug moves. Slowpoke's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 1,226. Slowpoke evolves into Slowbro, Slowking.
About: Slowpoke uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in water at the side of a river. However, this Pokémon often forgets what it's doing and often spends entire days just loafing at water's edge.

Name: slowbro
Summary: Slowbro is a Water & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Slowpoke. It is vulnerable to Ghost, Dark, Electric, Grass and Bug moves. Slowbro's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,545.
About: When it beats opponents with its bone, the cursed flames spread to them. No amount of water will stop those flames from burning.

Name: magnemite
Summary: Magnemite is an Electric & Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fire and Fighting moves. Magnemite's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,362. Magnemite evolves into Magneton.
About: Magnemite attaches itself to power lines to feed on electricity. If your house has a power outage, check your circuit breakers. You may find a large number of this Pokémon clinging to the breaker box.

Name: magneton
Summary: Magneton is an Electric & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Magnemite. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fire and Fighting moves. Magneton's strongest moveset is Spark & Zap Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,485. Magneton evolves into Magnezone.
About: Magneton emits a powerful magnetic force that is fatal to mechanical devices. As a result, large cities sound sirens to warn citizens of large-scale outbreaks of this Pokémon.

Name: farfetch'd
Summary: Farfetch'd is a regional Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Farfetch'd's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Leaf Blade and it has a Max CP of 1,236. This Pokémon is only found in Asia.
About: Farfetch'd is always seen with a stalk from a plant of some sort. Apparently, there are good stalks and bad stalks. This Pokémon has been known to fight with others over stalks.

Name: doduo
Summary: Doduo is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Doduo's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Drill Peck and it has a Max CP of 1,200. Doduo evolves into Dodrio.
About: Doduo's two heads never sleep at the same time. Its two heads take turns sleeping, so one head can always keep watch for enemies while the other one sleeps.

Name: dodrio
Summary: Dodrio is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Doduo. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Dodrio's strongest moveset is Steel Wing & Drill Peck and it has a Max CP of 2,362.
About: Watch out if Dodrio's three heads are looking in three separate directions. It's a sure sign that it is on its guard. Don't go near this Pokémon if it's being wary—it may decide to peck you.

Name: seel
Summary: Seel is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Seel's strongest moveset is Lick & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 971. Seel evolves into Dewgong.
About: Seel hunts for prey in the frigid sea underneath sheets of ice. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.

Name: dewgong
Summary: Dewgong is a Water & Ice Pokémon which evolves from Seel. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Dewgong's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 1,985.
About: Dewgong loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this Pokémon sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.

Name: grimer
Summary: Grimer is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Grimer's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,374. Grimer evolves into Muk.
About: Grimer's sludgy and rubbery body can be forced through any opening, however small it may be. This Pokémon enters sewer pipes to drink filthy wastewater.

Name: muk
Summary: Muk is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Grimer. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Muk's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 2,757.
About: From Muk's body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this Pokémon's body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.

Name: shellder
Summary: Shellder is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Shellder's strongest moveset is Tackle & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,080. Shellder evolves into Cloyster.
About: At night, this Pokémon uses its broad tongue to burrow a hole in the seafloor sand and then sleep in it. While it is sleeping, Shellder closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.

Name: cloyster
Summary: Cloyster is a Water & Ice Pokémon which evolves from Shellder. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Cloyster's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,547.
About: Cloyster is capable of swimming in the sea. It does so by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. This Pokémon shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.

Name: gastly
Summary: Gastly is a Ghost & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Ghost and Psychic moves. Gastly's strongest moveset is Lick & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,229. Gastly evolves into Haunter.
About: Gastly is largely composed of gaseous matter. When exposed to a strong wind, the gaseous body quickly dwindles away. Groups of this Pokémon cluster under the eaves of houses to escape the ravages of wind.

Name: haunter
Summary: Haunter is a Ghost & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Gastly. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Ghost and Psychic moves. Haunter's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,963. Haunter evolves into Gengar.
About: Haunter is a dangerous Pokémon. If one beckons you while floating in darkness, you must never approach it. This Pokémon will try to lick you with its tongue and steal your life away.

Name: gengar
Summary: Gengar is a Ghost & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Haunter. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Ghost and Psychic moves. Gengar's strongest moveset is Hex & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,878.
About: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a Gengar running past you, pretending to be your shadow.

Name: onix
Summary: Onix is a Rock & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Onix's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 1,101. Onix evolves into Steelix.
About: Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.

Name: drowzee
Summary: Drowzee is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Drowzee's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 1,040. Drowzee evolves into Hypno.
About: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that one of these Pokémon is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.

Name: hypno
Summary: Hypno is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Drowzee. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Hypno's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,090.
About: Hypno holds a pendulum in its hand. The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum lull the foe into a deep state of hypnosis. While this Pokémon searches for prey, it polishes the pendulum.

Name: krabby
Summary: Krabby is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Krabby's strongest moveset is Bubble & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,561. Krabby evolves into Kingler.
About: Krabby live on beaches, burrowed inside holes dug into the sand. On sandy beaches with little in the way of food, these Pokémon can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.

Name: kingler
Summary: Kingler is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Krabby. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Kingler's strongest moveset is Bubble & Crabhammer and it has a Max CP of 2,829.
About: Kingler has an enormous, oversized claw. It waves this huge claw in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, the Pokémon quickly tires.

Name: voltorb
Summary: Voltorb is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Voltorb's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,010. Voltorb evolves into Electrode.
About: Voltorb was first sighted at a company that manufactures Poké Balls. The link between that sighting and the fact that this Pokémon looks very similar to a Poké Ball remains a mystery.

Name: electrode
Summary: Electrode is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Voltorb. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Electrode's strongest moveset is Volt Switch & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 2,099.
About: Electrode eats electricity in the atmosphere. On days when lightning strikes, you can see this Pokémon exploding all over the place from eating too much electricity.

Name: exeggcute
Summary: Exeggcute is a Grass & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fire, Ice, Flying, Poison, Dark and Ghost moves. Exeggcute's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 1,175. Exeggcute evolves into Exeggutor.
About: This Pokémon consists of six eggs that form a closely knit cluster. The six eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear on the eggs, Exeggcute is close to evolution.

Name: exeggutor
Summary: Exeggutor is a Grass & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Exeggcute. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fire, Ice, Flying, Poison, Dark and Ghost moves. Exeggutor's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,014.
About: Exeggutor originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form Exeggcute.

Name: cubone
Summary: Cubone is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Cubone's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,019. Cubone evolves into Marowak.
About: Cubone pines for the mother it will never see again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in the full moon, it cries. The stains on the skull the Pokémon wears are made by the tears it sheds.

Name: marowak
Summary: Marowak is a Ground Pokémon which evolves from Cubone. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Marowak's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 1,835.
About: Marowak is the evolved form of a Cubone that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This Pokémon's tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.

Name: hitmonlee
Summary: Hitmonlee is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Hitmonlee's strongest moveset is Low Kick & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,576.
About: Hitmonlee's legs freely contract and stretch. Using these springlike legs, it bowls over foes with devastating kicks. After battle, it rubs down its legs and loosens the muscles to overcome fatigue.

Name: hitmonchan
Summary: Hitmonchan is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Hitmonchan's strongest moveset is Counter & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,332.
About: Hitmonchan is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who had been working toward a world championship. This Pokémon has an indomitable spirit and will never give up in the face of adversity.

Name: lickitung
Summary: Lickitung is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Lickitung's strongest moveset is Lick & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,411. Lickitung evolves into Lickilicky.
About: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.

Name: koffing
Summary: Koffing is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Koffing's strongest moveset is Infestation & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,214. Koffing evolves into Weezing.
About: If Koffing becomes agitated, it raises the toxicity of its internal gases and jets them out from all over its body. This Pokémon may also overinflate its round body, then explode.

Name: weezing
Summary: Weezing is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Koffing. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Weezing's strongest moveset is Infestation & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 2,293.
About: Weezing loves the gases given off by rotted kitchen garbage. This Pokémon will find a dirty, unkempt house and make it its home. At night, when the people in the house are asleep, it will go through the trash.

Name: rhyhorn
Summary: Rhyhorn is a Ground & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Rhyhorn's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,651. Rhyhorn evolves into Rhydon.
About: Rhyhorn runs in a straight line, smashing everything in its path. It is not bothered even if it rushes headlong into a block of steel. This Pokémon may feel some pain from the collision the next day, however.

Name: rhydon
Summary: Rhydon is a Ground & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Rhyhorn. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Rhydon's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 3,179. Rhydon evolves into Rhyperior.
About: Rhydon's horn can crush even uncut diamonds. One sweeping blow of its tail can topple a building. This Pokémon's hide is extremely tough. Even direct cannon hits don't leave a scratch.

Name: chansey
Summary: Chansey is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Happiny. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Chansey's strongest moveset is Pound & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,255. Chansey evolves into Blissey.
About: Chansey lays nutritionally excellent eggs on an everyday basis. The eggs are so delicious, they are easily and eagerly devoured by even those people who have lost their appetite.

Name: tangela
Summary: Tangela is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Tangela's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 2,238. Tangela evolves into Tangrowth.
About: Tangela's vines snap off easily if they are grabbed. This happens without pain, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by newly grown vines the very next day.

Name: kangaskhan
Summary: Kangaskhan is a regional Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Kangaskhan's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Return and it has a Max CP of 2,586. This Pokémon is only found in Australasia.
About: If you come across a young Kangaskhan playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby Pokémon's parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.

Name: horsea
Summary: Horsea is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Horsea's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,056. Horsea evolves into Seadra.
About: Horsea eats small insects and moss off of rocks. If the ocean current turns fast, this Pokémon anchors itself by wrapping its tail around rocks or coral to prevent being washed away.

Name: seadra
Summary: Seadra is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Horsea. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Seadra's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,093. Seadra evolves into Kingdra.
About: Seadra sleeps after wriggling itself between the branches of coral. Those trying to harvest coral are occasionally stung by this Pokémon's poison barbs if they fail to notice it.

Name: goldeen
Summary: Goldeen is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Goldeen's strongest moveset is Peck & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 1,152. Goldeen evolves into Seaking.
About: Goldeen is a very beautiful Pokémon with fins that billow elegantly in water. However, don't let your guard down around this Pokémon—it could ram you powerfully with its horn.

Name: seaking
Summary: Seaking is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Goldeen. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Seaking's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Megahorn and it has a Max CP of 2,162.
About: In the autumn, Seaking males can be seen performing courtship dances in riverbeds to woo females. During this season, this Pokémon's body coloration is at its most beautiful.

Name: staryu
Summary: Staryu is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Staryu's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,157. Staryu evolves into Starmie.
About: Staryu's center section has an organ called the core that shines bright red. If you go to a beach toward the end of summer, the glowing cores of these Pokémon look like the stars in the sky.

Name: starmie
Summary: Starmie is a Water & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Staryu. It is vulnerable to Ghost, Dark, Electric, Grass and Bug moves. Starmie's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,584.
About: Starmie's center section—the core—glows brightly in seven colors. Because of its luminous nature, this Pokémon has been given the nickname “the gem of the sea.”

Name: mr. mime
Summary: Mr. Mime is a regional Psychic & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Mime Jr.. It is vulnerable to Poison, Ghost and Steel moves. Mr. Mime's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,228. This Pokémon is only found in Europe.
About: Mr. Mime is a master of pantomime. Its gestures and motions convince watchers that something unseeable actually exists. Once the watchers are convinced, the unseeable thing exists as if it were real.

Name: scyther
Summary: Scyther is a Bug & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Scyther's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 2,706. Scyther evolves into Scizor.
About: Scyther is blindingly fast. Its blazing speed enhances the effectiveness of the twin scythes on its forearms. This Pokémon's scythes are so effective, they can slice through thick logs in one wicked stroke.

Name: jynx
Summary: Jynx is an Ice & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Smoochum. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Rock, Bug, Ghost and Steel moves. Jynx's strongest moveset is Confusion & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,555.
About: Jynx walks rhythmically, swaying and shaking its hips as if it were dancing. Its motions are so bouncingly alluring, people seeing it are compelled to shake their hips without giving any thought to what they are doing.

Name: electabuzz
Summary: Electabuzz is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Electabuzz's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 2,334. Electabuzz evolves into Electivire.
About: When a storm arrives, gangs of this Pokémon compete with each other to scale heights that are likely to be stricken by lightning bolts. Some towns use Electabuzz in place of lightning rods.

Name: magmar
Summary: Magmar is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Magmar's strongest moveset is Ember & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 2,394. Magmar evolves into Magmortar.
About: In battle, Magmar blows out intensely hot flames from all over its body to intimidate its opponent. This Pokémon's fiery bursts create heat waves that ignite grass and trees in its surroundings.

Name: pinsir
Summary: Pinsir is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Pinsir's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & X-Scissor and it has a Max CP of 2,959.
About: Pinsir is astoundingly strong. It can grip a foe weighing twice its weight in its horns and easily lift it. This Pokémon's movements turn sluggish in cold places.

Name: tauros
Summary: Tauros is a regional Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Tauros's strongest moveset is Tackle & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,620. This Pokémon is only found in North America.
About: This Pokémon is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for Tauros to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.

Name: magikarp
Summary: Magikarp is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Magikarp's strongest moveset is Splash & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 274. Magikarp evolves into Gyarados.
About: Magikarp is a pathetic excuse for a Pokémon that is only capable of flopping and splashing. This behavior prompted scientists to undertake research into it.

Name: gyarados
Summary: Gyarados is a Water & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Magikarp. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Gyarados's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 3,391.
About: When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon's wildly violent nature.

Name: lapras
Summary: Lapras is a Water & Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Lapras's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Surf and it has a Max CP of 2,641.
About: People have driven Lapras almost to the point of extinction. In the evenings, this Pokémon is said to sing plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind still remain.

Name: ditto
Summary: Ditto is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Ditto's strongest moveset is Transform & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 832.
About: Ditto rearranges its cell structure to transform itself into other shapes. However, if it tries to transform itself into something by relying on its memory, this Pokémon manages to get details wrong.

Name: eevee
Summary: Eevee is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Eevee's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Last Resort and it has a Max CP of 1,071. Eevee evolves into Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon.
About: Eevee has an unstable genetic makeup that suddenly mutates due to the environment in which it lives. Radiation from various stones causes this Pokémon to evolve.

Name: vaporeon
Summary: Vaporeon is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Vaporeon's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 3,114.
About: Vaporeon underwent a spontaneous mutation and grew fins and gills that allow it to live underwater. This Pokémon has the ability to freely control water.

Name: jolteon
Summary: Jolteon is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Jolteon's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 2,888.
About: Jolteon's cells generate a low level of electricity. This power is amplified by the static electricity of its fur, enabling the Pokémon to drop thunderbolts. The bristling fur is made of electrically charged needles.

Name: flareon
Summary: Flareon is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Flareon's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 3,029.
About: Flareon's fluffy fur has a functional purpose—it releases heat into the air so that its body does not get excessively hot. This Pokémon's body temperature can rise to a maximum of 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: porygon
Summary: Porygon is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Porygon's strongest moveset is Tackle & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,720. Porygon evolves into Porygon2.
About: Porygon is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data and entering cyberspace. This Pokémon is copy protected so it cannot be duplicated by copying.

Name: omanyte
Summary: Omanyte is a Rock & Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Omanyte's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,544. Omanyte evolves into Omastar.
About: Omanyte is one of the ancient and long-since-extinct Pokémon that have been regenerated from fossils by people. If attacked by an enemy, it withdraws itself inside its hard shell.

Name: omastar
Summary: Omastar is a Rock & Water Pokémon which evolves from Omanyte. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Omastar's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,786.
About: Omastar uses its tentacles to capture its prey. It is believed to have become extinct because its shell grew too large and heavy, causing its movements to become too slow and ponderous.

Name: kabuto
Summary: Kabuto is a Rock & Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Kabuto's strongest moveset is Scratch & Ancient Power and it has a Max CP of 1,370. Kabuto evolves into Kabutops.
About: Kabuto is a Pokémon that has been regenerated from a fossil. However, in extremely rare cases, living examples have been discovered. The Pokémon has not changed at all for 300 million years.

Name: kabutops
Summary: Kabutops is a Rock & Water Pokémon which evolves from Kabuto. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Kabutops's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 2,713.
About: Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.

Name: aerodactyl
Summary: Aerodactyl is a Rock & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Steel, Water and Electric moves. Aerodactyl's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 2,783.
About: Aerodactyl is a Pokémon from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from genetic material extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies in ancient times.

Name: snorlax
Summary: Snorlax is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Snorlax's strongest moveset is Lick & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,225.
About: Snorlax's typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile Pokémon that there are children who use its expansive belly as a place to play.

Name: articuno
Summary: Articuno is a legendary Ice & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Electric and Steel moves. Articuno's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,051.
About: Articuno is a Legendary Pokémon that can control ice. The flapping of its wings chills the air. As a result, it is said that when this Pokémon flies, snow will fall.

Name: zapdos
Summary: Zapdos is a legendary Electric & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice and Rock moves. Zapdos's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 3,527.
About: Zapdos is a Legendary Pokémon that has the ability to control electricity. It usually lives in thunderclouds. The Pokémon gains power if it is stricken by lightning bolts.

Name: moltres
Summary: Moltres is a legendary Fire & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Electric and Water moves. Moltres's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 3,465.
About: Moltres is a Legendary Pokémon that has the ability to control fire. If this Pokémon is injured, it is said to dip its body in the molten magma of a volcano to burn and heal itself.

Name: dratini
Summary: Dratini is a Dragon Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Dratini's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,004. Dratini evolves into Dragonair.
About: Dratini continually molts and sloughs off its old skin. It does so because the life energy within its body steadily builds to reach uncontrollable levels.

Name: dragonair
Summary: Dragonair is a Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Dratini. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Dragonair's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Dragon Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,780. Dragonair evolves into Dragonite.
About: Dragonair stores an enormous amount of energy inside its body. It is said to alter weather conditions in its vicinity by discharging energy from the crystals on its neck and tail.

Name: dragonite
Summary: Dragonite is a Dragon & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Dragonair. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy, Dragon and Rock moves. Dragonite's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Draco Meteor and it has a Max CP of 3,792.
About: Dragonite is capable of circling the globe in just 16 hours. It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.

Name: mewtwo
Summary: Mewtwo is a legendary Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Mewtwo's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 4,178.
About: Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon's body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.

Name: mew
Summary: Mew is a mythical Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Mew's strongest moveset is Snarl & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 3,265.
About: Mew is said to possess the genetic composition of all Pokémon. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.

Name: pichu
Summary: Pichu is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Pichu's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 473. Pichu evolves into Pikachu.
About: Pichu charges itself with electricity more easily on days with thunderclouds or when the air is very dry. You can hear the crackling of static electricity coming off this Pokémon.

Name: cleffa
Summary: Cleffa is a Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Cleffa's strongest moveset is Pound & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 671. Cleffa evolves into Clefairy.
About: On nights with many shooting stars, Cleffa can be seen dancing in a ring. They dance through the night and stop only at the break of day, when these Pokémon quench their thirst with the morning dew.

Name: igglybuff
Summary: Igglybuff is a Normal & Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Igglybuff's strongest moveset is Pound & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 535. Igglybuff evolves into Jigglypuff.
About: Igglybuff's vocal cords are not sufficiently developed. It would hurt its throat if it were to sing too much. This Pokémon gargles with freshwater from a clean stream.

Name: crobat
Summary: Crobat is a Poison & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Golbat. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Psychic and Electric moves. Crobat's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 2,646.
About: If this Pokémon is flying by fluttering only a pair of wings on either the forelegs or hind legs, it's proof that Crobat has been flying a long distance. It switches the wings it uses if it is tired.

Name: bellossom
Summary: Bellossom is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Gloom. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Bellossom's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Leaf Blade and it has a Max CP of 2,281.
About: When Bellossom gets exposed to plenty of sunlight, the leaves ringing its body begin to spin around. This Pokémon's dancing is renowned in the southern lands.

Name: politoed
Summary: Politoed is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Poliwhirl. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Politoed's strongest moveset is Bubble & Surf and it has a Max CP of 2,449.
About: The curled hair on Politoed's head is proof of its status as a king. It is said that the longer and more curled the hair, the more respect this Pokémon earns from its peers.

Name: slowking
Summary: Slowking is a Water & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Slowpoke. It is vulnerable to Ghost, Dark, Electric, Grass and Bug moves. Slowking's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,545.
About: Slowking undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this Pokémon apparently forgets everything it has learned if the Shellder on its head comes off.

Name: steelix
Summary: Steelix is a Steel & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Onix. It is vulnerable to Fire, Water, Ground and Fighting moves. Steelix's strongest moveset is Iron Tail & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,414.
About: Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth's core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.

Name: tyrogue
Summary: Tyrogue is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Tyrogue's strongest moveset is Rock Smash & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 492. Tyrogue evolves into Hitmonlee, Hitmonchan, Hitmontop.
About: Tyrogue becomes stressed out if it does not get to train every day. When raising this Pokémon, the Trainer must establish and uphold various training methods.

Name: hitmontop
Summary: Hitmontop is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Tyrogue. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Hitmontop's strongest moveset is Counter & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,156.
About: Hitmontop spins on its head at high speed, all the while delivering kicks. This technique is a remarkable mix of both offense and defense at the same time. The Pokémon travels faster spinning than it does walking.

Name: blissey
Summary: Blissey is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Chansey. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Blissey's strongest moveset is Pound & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,757.
About: Blissey senses sadness with its fluffy coat of fur. If it does so, this Pokémon will rush over to a sad person, no matter how far away, to share a Lucky Egg that brings a smile to any face.

Name: kingdra
Summary: Kingdra is a Water & Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Seadra. It is vulnerable to Fairy and Dragon moves. Kingdra's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Outrage and it has a Max CP of 2,641.
About: Kingdra lives at extreme ocean depths that are otherwise uninhabited. It has long been believed that the yawning of this Pokémon creates spiraling ocean currents.

Name: scizor
Summary: Scizor is a Bug & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Scyther. It is vulnerable to Fire moves. Scizor's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Iron Head and it has a Max CP of 3,001.
About: Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. This Pokémon flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.

Name: smoochum
Summary: Smoochum is an Ice & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Rock, Bug, Ghost and Steel moves. Smoochum's strongest moveset is Pound & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,291. Smoochum evolves into Jynx.
About: Smoochum actively runs about, but also falls quite often. Whenever the chance arrives, it will look for its reflection to make sure its face hasn't become dirty.

Name: elekid
Summary: Elekid is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Elekid's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,206. Elekid evolves into Electabuzz.
About: Elekid stores electricity in its body. If it touches metal and accidentally discharges all its built-up electricity, this Pokémon begins swinging its arms in circles to recharge itself.

Name: magby
Summary: Magby is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Magby's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,323. Magby evolves into Magmar.
About: Magby's state of health is determined by observing the fire it breathes. If the Pokémon is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.

Name: espeon
Summary: Espeon is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Espeon's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 3,170.
About: Espeon is extremely loyal to any Trainer it considers to be worthy. It is said that this Pokémon developed its precognitive powers to protect its Trainer from harm.

Name: umbreon
Summary: Umbreon is a Dark Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Umbreon's strongest moveset is Snarl & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 2,137.
About: Umbreon evolved as a result of exposure to the moon's waves. It hides silently in darkness and waits for its foes to make a move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.

Name: porygon2
Summary: Porygon2 is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Porygon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Porygon2's strongest moveset is Lock-On & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,711. Porygon2 evolves into Porygon-Z.
About: Porygon2 was created by humans using the power of science. The man-made Pokémon has been endowed with artificial intelligence that enables it to learn new gestures and emotions on its own.

Name: chikorita
Summary: Chikorita is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Chikorita's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 935. Chikorita evolves into Bayleef.
About: In battle, Chikorita waves its leaf around to keep the foe at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, becalming the battling Pokémon and creating a cozy, friendly atmosphere all around.

Name: bayleef
Summary: Bayleef is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Chikorita. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Bayleef's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,454. Bayleef evolves into Meganium.
About: Bayleef's neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each tubular leaf is a small shoot of a tree. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

Name: meganium
Summary: Meganium is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Bayleef. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Meganium's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Frenzy Plant and it has a Max CP of 2,410.
About: The fragrance of Meganium's flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe's fighting spirit.

Name: cyndaquil
Summary: Cyndaquil is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Cyndaquil's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 980. Cyndaquil evolves into Quilava.
About: Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames splutter fitfully with incomplete combustion.

Name: quilava
Summary: Quilava is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Cyndaquil. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Quilava's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,653. Quilava evolves into Typhlosion.
About: Quilava keeps its foes at bay with the intensity of its flames and gusts of superheated air. This Pokémon applies its outstanding nimbleness to dodge attacks even while scorching the foe with flames.

Name: typhlosion
Summary: Typhlosion is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Quilava. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Typhlosion's strongest moveset is Ember & Blast Burn and it has a Max CP of 2,889.
About: Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokémon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.

Name: totodile
Summary: Totodile is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Totodile's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,131. Totodile evolves into Croconaw.
About: Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile's jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.

Name: croconaw
Summary: Croconaw is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Totodile. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Croconaw's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,722. Croconaw evolves into Feraligatr.
About: Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.

Name: feraligatr
Summary: Feraligatr is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Croconaw. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Feraligatr's strongest moveset is Ice Fang & Hydro Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,857.
About: Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.

Name: sentret
Summary: Sentret is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Sentret's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 618. Sentret evolves into Furret.
About: When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.

Name: furret
Summary: Furret is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Sentret. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Furret's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,758.
About: Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.

Name: hoothoot
Summary: Hoothoot is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Hoothoot's strongest moveset is Peck & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 677. Hoothoot evolves into Noctowl.
About: Hoothoot has an internal organ that senses and tracks the earth's rotation. Using this special organ, this Pokémon begins hooting at precisely the same time every day.

Name: noctowl
Summary: Noctowl is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Hoothoot. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Noctowl's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 2,024.
About: Noctowl never fails at catching prey in darkness. This Pokémon owes its success to its superior vision that allows it to see in minimal light, and to its soft, supple wings that make no sound in flight.

Name: ledyba
Summary: Ledyba is a Bug & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Ledyba's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 728. Ledyba evolves into Ledian.
About: Ledyba secretes an aromatic fluid from where its legs join its body. This fluid is used for communicating with others. This Pokémon conveys its feelings to others by altering the fluid's scent.

Name: ledian
Summary: Ledian is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Ledyba. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Ledian's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,346.
About: It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live Ledian in countless numbers. There is a good reason for this—the Pokémon uses the light of the stars as its energy.

Name: spinarak
Summary: Spinarak is a Bug & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Spinarak's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Signal Beam and it has a Max CP of 816. Spinarak evolves into Ariados.
About: The web spun by Spinarak can be considered its second nervous system. It is said that this Pokémon can determine what kind of prey is touching its web just by the tiny vibrations it feels through the web's strands.

Name: ariados
Summary: Ariados is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Spinarak. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Ariados's strongest moveset is Infestation & Megahorn and it has a Max CP of 1,772.
About: Ariados's feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and vertical walls. This Pokémon constricts the foe with thin and strong silk webbing.

Name: chinchou
Summary: Chinchou is a Water & Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground and Grass moves. Chinchou's strongest moveset is Bubble & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,119. Chinchou evolves into Lanturn.
About: Chinchou lets loose positive and negative electrical charges from its two antennas to make its prey faint. This Pokémon flashes its electric lights to exchange signals with others.

Name: lanturn
Summary: Lanturn is a Water & Electric Pokémon which evolves from Chinchou. It is vulnerable to Ground and Grass moves. Lanturn's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 2,085.
About: Lanturn is nicknamed “the deep-sea star” for its illuminated antenna. This Pokémon produces light by causing a chemical reaction between bacteria and its bodily fluids inside the antenna.

Name: togepi
Summary: Togepi is a Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Togepi's strongest moveset is Hidden Power & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 657. Togepi evolves into Togetic.
About: As its energy, Togepi uses the positive emotions of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and Pokémon. This Pokémon stores up feelings of happiness inside its shell, then shares them with others.

Name: togetic
Summary: Togetic is a Fairy & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Togepi. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ice, Poison, Rock and Electric moves. Togetic's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 1,708. Togetic evolves into Togekiss.
About: Togetic is said to be a Pokémon that brings good fortune. When the Pokémon spots someone who is pure of heart, it is said to appear and share its happiness with that person.

Name: natu
Summary: Natu is a Psychic & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ice, Rock, Electric and Ghost moves. Natu's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Drill Peck and it has a Max CP of 1,102. Natu evolves into Xatu.
About: Natu cannot fly because its wings are not yet fully grown. If your eyes meet with this Pokémon's eyes, it will stare back intently at you. But if you move even slightly, it will hop away to safety.

Name: xatu
Summary: Xatu is a Psychic & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Natu. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ice, Rock, Electric and Ghost moves. Xatu's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Future Sight and it has a Max CP of 2,188.
About: Xatu stands rooted and still in one spot all day long. People believe that this Pokémon does so out of fear of the terrible things it has foreseen in the future.

Name: mareep
Summary: Mareep is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Mareep's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 991. Mareep evolves into Flaaffy.
About: Mareep's fluffy coat of wool rubs together and builds a static charge. The more static electricity is charged, the more brightly the lightbulb at the tip of its tail glows.

Name: flaaffy
Summary: Flaaffy is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Mareep. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Flaaffy's strongest moveset is Charge Beam & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,521. Flaaffy evolves into Ampharos.
About: Flaaffy's wool quality changes so that it can generate a high amount of static electricity with a small amount of wool. The bare and slick parts of its hide are shielded against electricity.

Name: ampharos
Summary: Ampharos is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Flaaffy. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Ampharos's strongest moveset is Volt Switch & Zap Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,852.
About: Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.

Name: marill
