Summary: Marill is a Water & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Azurill. It is vulnerable to Poison, Electric and Grass moves. Marill's strongest moveset is Bubble & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 461. Marill evolves into Azumarill.
About: Marill's oil-filled tail acts much like a life preserver. If you see just its tail bobbing on the water's surface, it's a sure indication that this Pokémon is diving beneath the water to feed on aquatic plants.

Name: azumarill
Summary: Azumarill is a Water & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Marill. It is vulnerable to Poison, Electric and Grass moves. Azumarill's strongest moveset is Bubble & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,588.
About: Azumarill's long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its hearing, this Pokémon can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and fast-running rivers.

Name: sudowoodo
Summary: Sudowoodo is a Rock Pokémon which evolves from Bonsly. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Sudowoodo's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 2,148.
About: Sudowoodo camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because its hands remain green throughout the year, the Pokémon is easily identified as a fake during the winter.

Name: hoppip
Summary: Hoppip is a Grass & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fire, Flying, Poison and Rock moves. Hoppip's strongest moveset is Bullet Seed & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 600. Hoppip evolves into Skiploom.
About: This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.

Name: skiploom
Summary: Skiploom is a Grass & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Hoppip. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fire, Flying, Poison and Rock moves. Skiploom's strongest moveset is Bullet Seed & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 976. Skiploom evolves into Jumpluff.
About: Skiploom's flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.

Name: jumpluff
Summary: Jumpluff is a Grass & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Skiploom. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fire, Flying, Poison and Rock moves. Jumpluff's strongest moveset is Infestation & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,636.
About: Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

Name: aipom
Summary: Aipom is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Aipom's strongest moveset is Scratch & Swift and it has a Max CP of 1,348. Aipom evolves into Ambipom.
About: Aipom's tail ends in a hand-like appendage that can be cleverly manipulated. However, because the Pokémon uses its tail so much, its real hands have become rather clumsy.

Name: sunkern
Summary: Sunkern is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Sunkern's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 395. Sunkern evolves into Sunflora.
About: Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.

Name: sunflora
Summary: Sunflora is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Sunkern. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Sunflora's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,141.
About: Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.

Name: yanma
Summary: Yanma is a Bug & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Yanma's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 1,470. Yanma evolves into Yanmega.
About: Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.

Name: wooper
Summary: Wooper is a Water & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Wooper's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Mud Bomb and it has a Max CP of 641. Wooper evolves into Quagsire.
About: Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.

Name: quagsire
Summary: Quagsire is a Water & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Wooper. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Quagsire's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 1,992.
About: Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon does not move, it does not get very hungry.

Name: murkrow
Summary: Murkrow is a Dark & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Ice, Electric and Rock moves. Murkrow's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 1,562. Murkrow evolves into Honchkrow.
About: Murkrow was feared and loathed as the alleged bearer of ill fortune. This Pokémon shows strong interest in anything that sparkles or glitters. It will even try to steal rings from women.

Name: misdreavus
Summary: Misdreavus is a Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Misdreavus's strongest moveset is Hex & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,926. Misdreavus evolves into Mismagius.
About: Misdreavus frightens people with a creepy, sobbing cry. The Pokémon apparently uses its red spheres to absorb the fearful feelings of foes and turn them into nutrition.

Name: unown
Summary: Unown is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Unown's strongest moveset is Hidden Power & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 1,185.
About: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

Name: wobbuffet
Summary: Wobbuffet is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Wobbuffet's strongest moveset is Counter & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,026.
About: If two or more Wobbuffet meet, they will turn competitive and try to outdo each other's endurance. However, they may try to see which one can endure the longest without food. Trainers need to beware of this habit.

Name: girafarig
Summary: Girafarig is a Normal & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug and Dark moves. Girafarig's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,046.
About: Girafarig's rear head also has a brain, but it is small. The rear head attacks in response to smells and sounds. Approaching this Pokémon from behind can cause the rear head to suddenly lash out and bite.

Name: pineco
Summary: Pineco is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Pineco's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Gyro Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,108. Pineco evolves into Forretress.
About: Pineco hangs from a tree branch and patiently waits for prey to come along. If the Pokémon is disturbed while eating by someone shaking its tree, it drops down to the ground and explodes with no warning.

Name: forretress
Summary: Forretress is a Bug & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Pineco. It is vulnerable to Fire moves. Forretress's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 2,282.
About: Forretress conceals itself inside its hardened steel shell. The shell is opened when the Pokémon is catching prey, but it does so at such a quick pace that the shell's inside cannot be seen.

Name: dunsparce
Summary: Dunsparce is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Dunsparce's strongest moveset is Bite & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 1,689.
About: Dunsparce has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backward. This Pokémon is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.

Name: gligar
Summary: Gligar is a Ground & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice and Water moves. Gligar's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,857. Gligar evolves into Gliscor.
About: Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.

Name: snubbull
Summary: Snubbull is a Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Snubbull's strongest moveset is Tackle & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 1,237. Snubbull evolves into Granbull.
About: By baring its fangs and making a scary face, Snubbull sends smaller Pokémon scurrying away in terror. However, this Pokémon seems a little sad at making its foes flee.

Name: granbull
Summary: Granbull is a Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Snubbull. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Granbull's strongest moveset is Charm & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 2,552.
About: Granbull has a particularly well-developed lower jaw. The enormous fangs are heavy, causing the Pokémon to tip its head back for balance. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite indiscriminately.

Name: qwilfish
Summary: Qwilfish is a Water & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Psychic and Electric moves. Qwilfish's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 2,051.
About: Qwilfish sucks in water, inflating itself. This Pokémon uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.

Name: shuckle
Summary: Shuckle is a Bug & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Rock and Steel moves. Shuckle's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 405.
About: Shuckle quietly hides itself under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its hard shell while eating berries it has stored away. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.

Name: heracross
Summary: Heracross is a regional Bug & Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Flying, Fairy, Psychic and Fire moves. Heracross's strongest moveset is Counter & Megahorn and it has a Max CP of 3,101. This Pokémon is only found in Latin America, south Florida, and Texas.
About: Heracross charges in a straight line at its foe, slips beneath the foe's grasp, and then scoops up and hurls the opponent with its mighty horn. This Pokémon even has enough power to topple a massive tree.

Name: sneasel
Summary: Sneasel is a Dark & Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Fairy, Bug, Steel, Fire and Rock moves. Sneasel's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,051. Sneasel evolves into Weavile.
About: Sneasel scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. This Pokémon seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.

Name: teddiursa
Summary: Teddiursa is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Teddiursa's strongest moveset is Scratch & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,328. Teddiursa evolves into Ursaring.
About: This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.

Name: ursaring
Summary: Ursaring is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Teddiursa. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Ursaring's strongest moveset is Counter & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,945.
About: In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.

Name: slugma
Summary: Slugma is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Slugma's strongest moveset is Ember & Flame Burst and it has a Max CP of 895. Slugma evolves into Magcargo.
About: Molten magma courses throughout Slugma's circulatory system. If this Pokémon is chilled, the magma cools and hardens. Its body turns brittle and chunks fall off, reducing its size.

Name: magcargo
Summary: Magcargo is a Fire & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Slugma. It is vulnerable to Water, Ground, Rock and Fighting moves. Magcargo's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 1,702.
About: Magcargo's shell is actually its skin that hardened as a result of cooling. Its shell is very brittle and fragile—just touching it causes it to crumble apart. This Pokémon returns to its original size by dipping itself in magma.

Name: swinub
Summary: Swinub is an Ice & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Grass, Water and Steel moves. Swinub's strongest moveset is Powder Snow & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 741. Swinub evolves into Piloswine.
About: Swinub roots for food by rubbing its snout against the ground. Its favorite food is a mushroom that grows under the cover of dead grass. This Pokémon occasionally roots out hot springs.

Name: piloswine
Summary: Piloswine is an Ice & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Swinub. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Grass, Water and Steel moves. Piloswine's strongest moveset is Ice Shard & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,345. Piloswine evolves into Mamoswine.
About: Piloswine is covered by a thick coat of long hair that enables it to endure the freezing cold. This Pokémon uses its tusks to dig up food that has been buried under ice.

Name: corsola
Summary: Corsola is a regional Water & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Corsola's strongest moveset is Bubble & Power Gem and it has a Max CP of 1,378. This Pokémon is only found in Tropics, near to the sea.
About: Corsola's branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night.

Name: remoraid
Summary: Remoraid is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Remoraid's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 912. Remoraid evolves into Octillery.
About: Remoraid sucks in water, then expels it at high velocity using its abdominal muscles to shoot down flying prey. When evolution draws near, this Pokémon travels downstream from rivers.

Name: octillery
Summary: Octillery is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Remoraid. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Octillery's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 2,315.
About: Octillery grabs onto its foe using its tentacles. This Pokémon tries to immobilize it before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, Octillery spews ink to escape.

Name: delibird
Summary: Delibird is an Ice & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Electric and Steel moves. Delibird's strongest moveset is Present & Ice Punch and it has a Max CP of 1,094.
About: Delibird carries its food bundled up in its tail. There once was a famous explorer who managed to reach the peak of the world's highest mountain, thanks to one of these Pokémon sharing its food.

Name: mantine
Summary: Mantine is a Water & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Mantyke. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Mantine's strongest moveset is Bubble & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 2,108.
About: On sunny days, schools of Mantine can be seen elegantly leaping over the sea's waves. This Pokémon is not bothered by the Remoraid that hitches rides.

Name: skarmory
Summary: Skarmory is a Steel & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire and Electric moves. Skarmory's strongest moveset is Steel Wing & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 2,108.
About: Skarmory is entirely encased in hard, protective armor. This Pokémon flies at close to 190 mph. It slashes foes with its wings that possess swordlike cutting edges.

Name: houndour
Summary: Houndour is a Dark & Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Ground, Rock and Water moves. Houndour's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,234. Houndour evolves into Houndoom.
About: Houndour hunt as a coordinated pack. They communicate with each other using a variety of cries to corner their prey. This Pokémon's remarkable teamwork is unparalleled.

Name: houndoom
Summary: Houndoom is a Dark & Fire Pokémon which evolves from Houndour. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Ground, Rock and Water moves. Houndoom's strongest moveset is Fire Fang & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 2,635.
About: In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokémon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

Name: phanpy
Summary: Phanpy is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Phanpy's strongest moveset is Tackle & Bulldoze and it has a Max CP of 1,206. Phanpy evolves into Donphan.
About: For its nest, Phanpy digs a vertical pit in the ground at the edge of a river. It marks the area around its nest with its trunk to let the others know that the area has been claimed.

Name: donphan
Summary: Donphan is a Ground Pokémon which evolves from Phanpy. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Donphan's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 3,013.
About: Donphan's favorite attack is curling its body into a ball, then charging at its foe while rolling at high speed. Once it starts rolling, this Pokémon can't stop very easily.

Name: stantler
Summary: Stantler is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Stantler's strongest moveset is Tackle & Return and it has a Max CP of 2,164.
About: Stantler's magnificent antlers were traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction by those who were after the priceless antlers.

Name: smeargle
Summary: Smeargle is an unobtainable Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves.
About: Smeargle marks the boundaries of its territory using a body fluid that leaks out from the tip of its tail. Over 5,000 different marks left by this Pokémon have been found.

Name: miltank
Summary: Miltank is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Miltank's strongest moveset is Tackle & Body Slam and it has a Max CP of 2,354.
About: Miltank gives over five gallons of milk on a daily basis. Its sweet milk is enjoyed by children and grown-ups alike. People who can't drink milk turn it into yogurt and eat it instead.

Name: raikou
Summary: Raikou is a legendary Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Raikou's strongest moveset is Volt Switch & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 3,452.
About: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

Name: entei
Summary: Entei is a legendary Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Entei's strongest moveset is Fire Fang & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 3,473.
About: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

Name: suicune
Summary: Suicune is a legendary Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Suicune's strongest moveset is Snarl & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,983.
About: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

Name: larvitar
Summary: Larvitar is a Rock & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Larvitar's strongest moveset is Bite & Ancient Power and it has a Max CP of 1,040. Larvitar evolves into Pupitar.
About: Larvitar is born deep under the ground. To come up to the surface, this Pokémon must eat its way through the soil above. Until it does so, Larvitar cannot see its parents.

Name: pupitar
Summary: Pupitar is a Rock & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Larvitar. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Pupitar's strongest moveset is Bite & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,766. Pupitar evolves into Tyranitar.
About: Pupitar creates a gas inside its body that it compresses and forcefully ejects to propel itself like a jet. The body is very durable—it avoids damage even if it hits solid steel.

Name: tyranitar
Summary: Tyranitar is a Rock & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Pupitar. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Fairy, Ground, Bug, Steel, Water and Grass moves. Tyranitar's strongest moveset is Smack Down & Return and it has a Max CP of 3,834.
About: Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. This Pokémon wanders about in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.

Name: lugia
Summary: Lugia is a legendary Psychic & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ice, Rock, Electric and Ghost moves. Lugia's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 3,703.
About: Lugia's wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

Name: ho-oh
Summary: Ho-Oh is a legendary Fire & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Electric and Water moves. Ho-Oh's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 3,863.
About: Ho-Oh's feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

Name: celebi
Summary: Celebi is a mythical Psychic & Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fire, Ice, Flying, Poison, Dark and Ghost moves. Celebi's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 3,265.
About: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

Name: azurill
Summary: Azurill is a Normal & Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Azurill's strongest moveset is Bubble & Body Slam and it has a Max CP of 364. Azurill evolves into Marill.
About: Azurill spins its tail as if it were a lasso, then hurls it far. The momentum of the throw sends its body flying, too. Using this unique action, one of these Pokémon managed to hurl itself a record 33 feet.

Name: wynaut
Summary: Wynaut is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Wynaut's strongest moveset is Counter & Mirror Coat and it has a Max CP of 534. Wynaut evolves into Wobbuffet.
About: Wynaut can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this Pokémon will be slapping the ground with its tail.

Name: treecko
Summary: Treecko is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Treecko's strongest moveset is Pound & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,053. Treecko evolves into Grovyle.
About: Treecko has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This Pokémon attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

Name: grovyle
Summary: Grovyle is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Treecko. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Grovyle's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,673. Grovyle evolves into Sceptile.
About: The leaves growing out of Grovyle's body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

Name: sceptile
Summary: Sceptile is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Grovyle. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Sceptile's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Frenzy Plant and it has a Max CP of 2,757.
About: The leaves growing on Sceptile's body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile—it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

Name: torchic
Summary: Torchic is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Torchic's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,093. Torchic evolves into Combusken.
About: Torchic sticks with its Trainer, following behind with unsteady steps. This Pokémon breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.

Name: combusken
Summary: Combusken is a Fire & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Torchic. It is vulnerable to Flying, Ground, Psychic and Water moves. Combusken's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,652. Combusken evolves into Blaziken.
About: Combusken toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This Pokémon's legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out 10 kicks in one second.

Name: blaziken
Summary: Blaziken is a Fire & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Combusken. It is vulnerable to Flying, Ground, Psychic and Water moves. Blaziken's strongest moveset is Counter & Blast Burn and it has a Max CP of 2,848.
About: In battle, Blaziken blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this Pokémon's wrists burn.

Name: mudkip
Summary: Mudkip is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Mudkip's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,128. Mudkip evolves into Marshtomp.
About: The fin on Mudkip's head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

Name: marshtomp
Summary: Marshtomp is a Water & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Mudkip. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Marshtomp's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Surf and it has a Max CP of 1,776. Marshtomp evolves into Swampert.
About: The surface of Marshtomp's body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This Pokémon plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

Name: swampert
Summary: Swampert is a Water & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Marshtomp. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Swampert's strongest moveset is Mud Shot & Hydro Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,974.
About: Swampert is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This Pokémon also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.

Name: poochyena
Summary: Poochyena is a Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Poochyena's strongest moveset is Snarl & Crunch and it has a Max CP of 678. Poochyena evolves into Mightyena.
About: At first sight, Poochyena takes a bite at anything that moves. This Pokémon chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.

Name: mightyena
Summary: Mightyena is a Dark Pokémon which evolves from Poochyena. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Mightyena's strongest moveset is Bite & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,926.
About: Mightyena gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This Pokémon will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.

Name: zigzagoon
Summary: Zigzagoon is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Zigzagoon's strongest moveset is Tackle & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 508. Zigzagoon evolves into Linoone.
About: Zigzagoon restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This Pokémon does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.

Name: linoone
Summary: Linoone is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Zigzagoon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Linoone's strongest moveset is Tackle & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,662.
About: Linoone always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This Pokémon is very challenged by gently curving roads.

Name: wurmple
Summary: Wurmple is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Wurmple's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 578. Wurmple evolves into Silcoon, Cascoon.
About: Using the spikes on its rear end, Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokémon's feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.

Name: silcoon
Summary: Silcoon is a Bug Pokémon which evolves from Wurmple. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Silcoon's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 553. Silcoon evolves into Beautifly.
About: Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.

Name: cascoon
Summary: Cascoon is a Bug Pokémon which evolves from Wurmple. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Cascoon's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 553. Cascoon evolves into Dustox.
About: Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.

Name: beautifly
Summary: Beautifly is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Silcoon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Beautifly's strongest moveset is Infestation & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,765.
About: Beautifly's favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokémon, just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.

Name: dustox
Summary: Dustox is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Cascoon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Dustox's strongest moveset is Confusion & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,224.
About: Dustox is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this Pokémon are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.

Name: lotad
Summary: Lotad is a Water & Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Flying, Poison and Bug moves. Lotad's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Energy Ball and it has a Max CP of 598. Lotad evolves into Lombre.
About: Lotad live in ponds and lakes, where they float on the surface. It grows weak if its broad leaf dies. On rare occasions, this Pokémon travels on land in search of clean water.

Name: lombre
Summary: Lombre is a Water & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Lotad. It is vulnerable to Flying, Poison and Bug moves. Lombre's strongest moveset is Bubble & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,197. Lombre evolves into Ludicolo.
About: Lombre is nocturnal—it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief maker. When this Pokémon spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.

Name: ludicolo
Summary: Ludicolo is a Water & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Lombre. It is vulnerable to Flying, Poison and Bug moves. Ludicolo's strongest moveset is Bubble & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,323.
About: Ludicolo begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This Pokémon is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.

Name: seedot
Summary: Seedot is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Seedot's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 598. Seedot evolves into Nuzleaf.
About: Seedot attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this Pokémon's body becomes.

Name: nuzleaf
Summary: Nuzleaf is a Grass & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Seedot. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fairy, Ice, Fighting, Fire, Poison and Flying moves. Nuzleaf's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,227. Nuzleaf evolves into Shiftry.
About: Nuzleaf live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This Pokémon dislikes having its long nose pinched.

Name: shiftry
Summary: Shiftry is a Grass & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Nuzleaf. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fairy, Ice, Fighting, Fire, Poison and Flying moves. Shiftry's strongest moveset is Snarl & Leaf Blade and it has a Max CP of 2,333.
About: Shiftry is a mysterious Pokémon that is said to live atop towering trees dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.

Name: taillow
Summary: Taillow is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Taillow's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 765. Taillow evolves into Swellow.
About: Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokémon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

Name: swellow
Summary: Swellow is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Taillow. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Swellow's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 1,920.
About: Swellow flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokémon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow's clawed feet, preventing escape.

Name: wingull
Summary: Wingull is a Water & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Wingull's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 765. Wingull evolves into Pelipper.
About: Wingull has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This Pokémon rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.

Name: pelipper
Summary: Pelipper is a Water & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Wingull. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Pelipper's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,127.
About: Pelipper is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon and eggs inside its massive bill. This Pokémon builds its nest on steep cliffs facing the sea.

Name: ralts
Summary: Ralts is a Psychic & Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Poison, Ghost and Steel moves. Ralts's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psyshock and it has a Max CP of 539. Ralts evolves into Kirlia.
About: Ralts senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This Pokémon rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.

Name: kirlia
Summary: Kirlia is a Psychic & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Ralts. It is vulnerable to Poison, Ghost and Steel moves. Kirlia's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 966. Kirlia evolves into Gallade, Gardevoir.
About: It is said that a Kirlia that is exposed to the positive emotions of its Trainer grows beautiful. This Pokémon controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.

Name: gardevoir
Summary: Gardevoir is a Psychic & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Kirlia. It is vulnerable to Poison, Ghost and Steel moves. Gardevoir's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 3,093.
About: Gardevoir has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its Trainer, this Pokémon is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.

Name: surskit
Summary: Surskit is a Bug & Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Flying, Rock and Electric moves. Surskit's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Signal Beam and it has a Max CP of 791. Surskit evolves into Masquerain.
About: From the tips of its feet, Surskit secretes an oil that enables it to walk on water as if it were skating. This Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms in ponds and lakes.

Name: masquerain
Summary: Masquerain is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Surskit. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Masquerain's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Silver Wind and it has a Max CP of 2,270.
About: Masquerain intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns on its antennas. This Pokémon flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction—even sideways and backwards—as if it were a helicopter.

Name: shroomish
Summary: Shroomish is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Shroomish's strongest moveset is Bullet Seed & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 810. Shroomish evolves into Breloom.
About: Shroomish live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This Pokémon feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.

Name: breloom
Summary: Breloom is a Grass & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Shroomish. It is vulnerable to Flying, Fairy, Psychic, Ice, Fire and Poison moves. Breloom's strongest moveset is Counter & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 2,628.
About: Breloom closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This Pokémon's fighting technique puts boxers to shame.

Name: slakoth
Summary: Slakoth is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Slakoth's strongest moveset is Yawn & Body Slam and it has a Max CP of 1,002. Slakoth evolves into Vigoroth.
About: Slakoth lolls around for over 20 hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This Pokémon's sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.

Name: vigoroth
Summary: Vigoroth is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Slakoth. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Vigoroth's strongest moveset is Scratch & Body Slam and it has a Max CP of 1,968. Vigoroth evolves into Slaking.
About: Vigoroth is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply can't tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This Pokémon's stress level rises if it can't be moving constantly.

Name: slaking
Summary: Slaking is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Vigoroth. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Slaking's strongest moveset is Yawn & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 4,431.
About: Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this Pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.

Name: nincada
Summary: Nincada is an unobtainable Bug & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Water, Flying and Ice moves. Nincada's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 768. Nincada evolves into Ninjask, Shedinja.
About: Nincada lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This Pokémon absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.

Name: ninjask
Summary: Ninjask is an unobtainable Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Nincada. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Ninjask's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,969.
About: Ninjask moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this Pokémon was long believed to be invisible.

Name: shedinja
Summary: Shedinja is an unobtainable Bug & Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Nincada. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Dark, Rock and Ghost moves. Shedinja's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 393.
About: Shedinja's hard body doesn't move—not even a twitch. In fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this Pokémon will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.

Name: whismur
Summary: Whismur is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Whismur's strongest moveset is Pound & Stomp and it has a Max CP of 671. Whismur evolves into Loudred.
About: Normally, Whismur's voice is very quiet—it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this Pokémon senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.

Name: loudred
Summary: Loudred is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Whismur. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Loudred's strongest moveset is Bite & Stomp and it has a Max CP of 1,327. Loudred evolves into Exploud.
About: Loudred's bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. It uses its voice to punish its foes. This Pokémon's round ears serve as loudspeakers.

Name: exploud
Summary: Exploud is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Loudred. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Exploud's strongest moveset is Bite & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 2,347.
About: Exploud triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. If this Pokémon violently inhales from the ports on its body, it's a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.

Name: makuhita
Summary: Makuhita is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Makuhita's strongest moveset is Rock Smash & Cross Chop and it has a Max CP of 817. Makuhita evolves into Hariyama.
About: Makuhita is tenacious—it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this Pokémon stores more energy in its body for evolving.

Name: hariyama
Summary: Hariyama is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Makuhita. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Hariyama's strongest moveset is Counter & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 2,829.
About: Hariyama practices its straight-arm slaps in any number of locations. One hit of this Pokémon's powerful, openhanded, straight-arm punches could snap a telephone pole in two.

Name: nosepass
Summary: Nosepass is a Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Nosepass's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 993. Nosepass evolves into Probopass.
About: Nosepass's magnetic nose is always pointed to the north. If two of these Pokémon meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they are close because their magnetic noses repel one another.

Name: skitty
Summary: Skitty is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Skitty's strongest moveset is Tackle & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 739. Skitty evolves into Delcatty.
About: Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.

Name: delcatty
Summary: Delcatty is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Skitty. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Delcatty's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 1,496.
About: Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.

Name: sableye
Summary: Sableye is a Dark & Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy moves. Sableye's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 1,476.
About: Sableye lead quiet lives deep inside caverns. They are feared, however, because these Pokémon are thought to steal the spirits of people when their eyes burn with a sinister glow in the darkness.

Name: mawile
Summary: Mawile is a Steel & Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire and Ground moves. Mawile's strongest moveset is Fire Fang & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,634.
About: Mawile's huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, Mawile chomps it with its gaping jaws.

Name: aron
Summary: Aron is a Steel & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting and Water moves. Aron's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Iron Head and it has a Max CP of 1,307. Aron evolves into Lairon.
About: This Pokémon has a body of steel. To make its body, Aron feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.

Name: lairon
Summary: Lairon is a Steel & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Aron. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting and Water moves. Lairon's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 2,056. Lairon evolves into Aggron.
About: Lairon tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This Pokémon makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.

Name: aggron
Summary: Aggron is a Steel & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Lairon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting and Water moves. Aggron's strongest moveset is Iron Tail & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 3,000.
About: Aggron claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This Pokémon vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.

Name: meditite
Summary: Meditite is a Fighting & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Ghost moves. Meditite's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psyshock and it has a Max CP of 693. Meditite evolves into Medicham.
About: Meditite undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this Pokémon always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.

Name: medicham
Summary: Medicham is a Fighting & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Meditite. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Ghost moves. Medicham's strongest moveset is Counter & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 1,431.
About: It is said that through meditation, Medicham heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This Pokémon hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.

Name: electrike
Summary: Electrike is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Electrike's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 965. Electrike evolves into Manectric.
About: Electrike stores electricity in its long body hair. This Pokémon stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.

Name: manectric
Summary: Manectric is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Electrike. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Manectric's strongest moveset is Snarl & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 2,340.
About: Manectric is constantly discharging electricity from its mane. The sparks sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this Pokémon creates thunderclouds.

Name: plusle
Summary: Plusle is a regional Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Plusle's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,778. This Pokémon is only found in North America, South America, Africa.
About: Plusle always acts as a cheerleader for its partners. Whenever a teammate puts out a good effort in battle, this Pokémon shorts out its body to create the crackling noises of sparks to show its joy.

Name: minun
Summary: Minun is a regional Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Minun's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,694. This Pokémon is only found in Europe, Asia, Australasia.
About: Minun is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.

Name: volbeat
Summary: Volbeat is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Volbeat's strongest moveset is Struggle Bug & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,771.
About: With the arrival of night, Volbeat emits light from its tail. It communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. This Pokémon is attracted by the sweet aroma of Illumise.

Name: illumise
Summary: Illumise is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Illumise's strongest moveset is Struggle Bug & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,771.
About: Illumise attracts a swarm of Volbeat using a sweet fragrance. Once the Volbeat have gathered, this Pokémon leads the lit-up swarm in drawing geometric designs on the canvas of the night sky.

Name: roselia
Summary: Roselia is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Budew. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Roselia's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,870. Roselia evolves into Roserade.
About: Roselia shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this Pokémon brings serenity to living things.

Name: gulpin
Summary: Gulpin is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Gulpin's strongest moveset is Pound & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 866. Gulpin evolves into Swalot.
About: Virtually all of Gulpin's body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This Pokémon's stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.

Name: swalot
Summary: Swalot is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Gulpin. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Swalot's strongest moveset is Infestation & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,978.
About: When Swalot spots prey, it spurts out a hideously toxic fluid from its pores and sprays the target. Once the prey has weakened, this Pokémon gulps it down whole with its cavernous mouth.

Name: carvanha
Summary: Carvanha is a Water & Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Bug, Electric, Grass and Fighting moves. Carvanha's strongest moveset is Snarl & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,020. Carvanha evolves into Sharpedo.
About: Carvanha's strongly developed jaws and its sharply pointed fangs pack the destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and sunk by this Pokémon.

Name: sharpedo
Summary: Sharpedo is a Water & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Carvanha. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Bug, Electric, Grass and Fighting moves. Sharpedo's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,181.
About: Nicknamed “the bully of the sea,” Sharpedo is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these Pokémon can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.

Name: wailmer
Summary: Wailmer is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Wailmer's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 1,468. Wailmer evolves into Wailord.
About: Wailmer's nostrils are located above its eyes. This playful Pokémon loves to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body out of its nostrils.

Name: wailord
Summary: Wailord is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Wailmer. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Wailord's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Surf and it has a Max CP of 2,280.
About: Wailord is the largest of all identified Pokémon up to now. This giant Pokémon swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.

Name: numel
Summary: Numel is a Fire & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water and Ground moves. Numel's strongest moveset is Ember & Bulldoze and it has a Max CP of 1,057. Numel evolves into Camerupt.
About: Numel is extremely dull witted—it doesn't notice being hit. However, it can't stand hunger for even a second. This Pokémon's body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

Name: camerupt
Summary: Camerupt is a Fire & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Numel. It is vulnerable to Water and Ground moves. Camerupt's strongest moveset is Ember & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 2,193.
About: Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokémon's back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

Name: torkoal
Summary: Torkoal is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Torkoal's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 2,093.
About: Torkoal digs through mountains in search of coal. If it finds some, it fills hollow spaces on its shell with the coal and burns it. If it is attacked, this Pokémon spouts thick black smoke to beat a retreat.

Name: spoink
Summary: Spoink is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Spoink's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,334. Spoink evolves into Grumpig.
About: Spoink bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. As a result, this Pokémon cannot afford to stop bouncing—if it stops, its heart will stop.

Name: grumpig
Summary: Grumpig is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Spoink. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Grumpig's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,369.
About: Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. When this Pokémon uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.

Name: spinda
Summary: Spinda is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Spinda's strongest moveset is Sucker Punch & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,220.
About: All the Spinda that exist in the world are said to have utterly unique spot patterns. The shaky, tottering steps of this Pokémon give it the appearance of dancing.

Name: trapinch
Summary: Trapinch is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Trapinch's strongest moveset is Mud Shot & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,274. Trapinch evolves into Vibrava.
About: Trapinch's nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit dug in sand. This Pokémon patiently waits for prey to tumble down the pit. Its giant jaws have enough strength to crush even boulders.

Name: vibrava
Summary: Vibrava is a Ground & Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Trapinch. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy and Dragon moves. Vibrava's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,225. Vibrava evolves into Flygon.
About: To make prey faint, Vibrava generates ultrasonic waves by vigorously making its two wings vibrate. This Pokémon's ultrasonic waves are so powerful, they can bring on headaches in people.

Name: flygon
Summary: Flygon is a Ground & Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Vibrava. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy and Dragon moves. Flygon's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,661.
About: Flygon is nicknamed “the elemental spirit of the desert.” Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this Pokémon is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.

Name: cacnea
Summary: Cacnea is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Cacnea's strongest moveset is Sucker Punch & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,242. Cacnea evolves into Cacturne.
About: Cacnea lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this Pokémon shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.

Name: cacturne
Summary: Cacturne is a Grass & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Cacnea. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fairy, Ice, Fighting, Fire, Poison and Flying moves. Cacturne's strongest moveset is Sucker Punch & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 2,298.
About: During the daytime, Cacturne remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This Pokémon becomes active at night when the temperature drops.

Name: swablu
Summary: Swablu is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Swablu's strongest moveset is Peck & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 824. Swablu evolves into Altaria.
About: Swablu has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. This Pokémon is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.

Name: altaria
Summary: Altaria is a Dragon & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Swablu. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy, Dragon and Rock moves. Altaria's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 2,004.
About: Altaria dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this Pokémon makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.

Name: zangoose
Summary: Zangoose is a regional Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Zangoose's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,418. This Pokémon is only found in Europe, Asia, Australasia.
About: Memories of battling its archrival Seviper are etched into every cell of Zangoose's body. This Pokémon adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.

Name: seviper
Summary: Seviper is a regional Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Seviper's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Crunch and it has a Max CP of 2,105. This Pokémon is only found in North America, South America, Africa.
About: Seviper shares a generations-long feud with Zangoose. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This Pokémon attacks using its sword-edged tail.

Name: lunatone
Summary: Lunatone is a Rock & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Bug, Ghost, Steel, Water and Grass moves. Lunatone's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,327.
About: Lunatone was discovered at a location where a meteoroid fell. As a result, some people theorize that this Pokémon came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.

Name: solrock
Summary: Solrock is a Rock & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Bug, Ghost, Steel, Water and Grass moves. Solrock's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,327.
About: Solrock is a new species of Pokémon that is said to have fallen from space. It floats in air and moves silently. In battle, this Pokémon releases intensely bright light.

Name: barboach
Summary: Barboach is a Water & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Barboach's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 819. Barboach evolves into Whiscash.
About: Barboach's sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. This Pokémon hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.

Name: whiscash
Summary: Whiscash is a Water & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Barboach. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Whiscash's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Mud Bomb and it has a Max CP of 2,075.
About: Whiscash is extremely territorial. Just one of these Pokémon will claim a large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes about and triggers a massive earthquake.

Name: corphish
Summary: Corphish is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Corphish's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,230. Corphish evolves into Crawdaunt.
About: Corphish were originally foreign Pokémon that were imported as pets. They eventually turned up in the wild. This Pokémon is very hardy and has greatly increased its population.

Name: crawdaunt
Summary: Crawdaunt is a Water & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Corphish. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Bug, Electric, Grass and Fighting moves. Crawdaunt's strongest moveset is Snarl & Crabhammer and it has a Max CP of 2,474.
About: Crawdaunt has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this Pokémon, making them desolate places.

Name: baltoy
Summary: Baltoy is a Ground & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Dark, Ice, Grass, Bug and Ghost moves. Baltoy's strongest moveset is Confusion & Dig and it has a Max CP of 787. Baltoy evolves into Claydol.
About: Baltoy moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this Pokémon living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.

Name: claydol
Summary: Claydol is a Ground & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Baltoy. It is vulnerable to Water, Dark, Ice, Grass, Bug and Ghost moves. Claydol's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 1,971.
About: Claydol are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This Pokémon moves about while levitating.

Name: lileep
Summary: Lileep is a Rock & Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Ice, Bug and Steel moves. Lileep's strongest moveset is Infestation & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,291. Lileep evolves into Cradily.
About: Lileep became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient Pokémon attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles shaped like flower petals.

Name: cradily
Summary: Cradily is a Rock & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Lileep. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Ice, Bug and Steel moves. Cradily's strongest moveset is Infestation & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 2,211.
About: Cradily roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This Pokémon freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.

Name: anorith
Summary: Anorith is a Rock & Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Rock and Steel moves. Anorith's strongest moveset is Struggle Bug & Ancient Power and it has a Max CP of 1,529. Anorith evolves into Armaldo.
About: Anorith was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive Pokémon once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.

Name: armaldo
Summary: Armaldo is a Rock & Bug Pokémon which evolves from Anorith. It is vulnerable to Water, Rock and Steel moves. Armaldo's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Rock Blast and it has a Max CP of 2,848.
About: Armaldo's tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This Pokémon's two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.

Name: feebas
Summary: Feebas is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Feebas's strongest moveset is Tackle & Mirror Coat and it has a Max CP of 274. Feebas evolves into Milotic.
About: Feebas's fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this Pokémon is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.

Name: milotic
Summary: Milotic is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Feebas. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Milotic's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Surf and it has a Max CP of 3,005.
About: Milotic is said to be the most beautiful of all the Pokémon. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.

Name: castform
Summary: Castform (Normal) is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Castform's strongest moveset is Tackle & Weather Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,632.
About: Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

Name: kecleon
Summary: Kecleon is an unobtainable Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Kecleon's strongest moveset is Lick & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 2,047.
About: Kecleon is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception—this Pokémon can't change the zigzag pattern on its belly.

Name: shuppet
Summary: Shuppet is a Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Shuppet's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,018. Shuppet evolves into Banette.
About: Shuppet is attracted by feelings of jealousy and vindictiveness. If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this Pokémon will appear in a swarm and line up beneath the eaves of that person's home.

Name: banette
Summary: Banette is a Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Shuppet. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Banette's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,298.
About: Banette generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This Pokémon was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.

Name: duskull
Summary: Duskull is a Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Duskull's strongest moveset is Hex & Return and it has a Max CP of 706. Duskull evolves into Dusclops.
About: Duskull can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this Pokémon chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.

Name: dusclops
Summary: Dusclops is a Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Duskull. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Dusclops's strongest moveset is Hex & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,591. Dusclops evolves into Dusknoir.
About: Dusclops's body is completely hollow—there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This Pokémon will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.

Name: tropius
Summary: Tropius is a Grass & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fire, Flying, Poison and Rock moves. Tropius's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Leaf Blade and it has a Max CP of 1,941.
About: The bunches of fruit around Tropius's neck are very popular with children. This Pokémon loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.

Name: chimecho
Summary: Chimecho is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Chingling. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Chimecho's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,259.
About: Chimecho makes its cries echo inside its hollow body. When this Pokémon becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have the power to knock foes flying.

Name: absol
Summary: Absol is a Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Absol's strongest moveset is Snarl & Dark Pulse and it has a Max CP of 2,526.
About: Every time Absol appears before people, it is followed by a disaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the disaster Pokémon.

Name: snorunt
Summary: Snorunt is an Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Snorunt's strongest moveset is Powder Snow & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 888. Snorunt evolves into Glalie, Froslass.
About: Snorunt live in regions with heavy snowfall. In seasons without snow, such as spring and summer, this Pokémon steals away to live quietly among stalactites and stalagmites deep in caverns.

Name: glalie
Summary: Glalie is an Ice Pokémon which evolves from Snorunt. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Glalie's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,105.
About: Glalie has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This Pokémon has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.

Name: spheal
Summary: Spheal is an Ice & Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Spheal's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aurora Beam and it has a Max CP of 962. Spheal evolves into Sealeo.
About: Spheal is much faster rolling than walking to get around. When groups of this Pokémon eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.

Name: sealeo
Summary: Sealeo is an Ice & Water Pokémon which evolves from Spheal. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Sealeo's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aurora Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,714. Sealeo evolves into Walrein.
About: Sealeo has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This Pokémon occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a Spheal on its nose.

Name: walrein
Summary: Walrein is an Ice & Water Pokémon which evolves from Sealeo. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Walrein's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 2,726.
About: Walrein's two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing 10 tons with one blow. This Pokémon's thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.

Name: clamperl
Summary: Clamperl is an unobtainable Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Clamperl's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,270. Clamperl evolves into Huntail, Gorebyss.
About: Clamperl's sturdy shell is not only good for protection—it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown Clamperl's shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.

Name: huntail
Summary: Huntail is an unobtainable Water Pokémon which evolves from Clamperl. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Huntail's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 2,340.
About: Huntail's presence went unnoticed by people for a long time because it lives at extreme depths in the sea. This Pokémon's eyes can see clearly even in the murky dark depths of the ocean.

Name: gorebyss
Summary: Gorebyss is an unobtainable Water Pokémon which evolves from Clamperl. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Gorebyss's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,494.
About: Gorebyss lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this Pokémon's body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.

Name: relicanth
Summary: Relicanth is a regional Water & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Relicanth's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,528. This Pokémon is only found in New Zealand and the surrounding islands.
About: Relicanth is a Pokémon species that existed for a hundred million years without ever changing its form. This ancient Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms with its toothless mouth.

Name: luvdisc
Summary: Luvdisc is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Luvdisc's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 848.
About: Luvdisc live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped Pokémon earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean's waves.

Name: bagon
Summary: Bagon is a Dragon Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Bagon's strongest moveset is Bite & Return and it has a Max CP of 1,156. Bagon evolves into Shelgon.
About: Bagon has a dream of one day soaring in the sky. In doomed efforts to fly, this Pokémon hurls itself off cliffs. As a result of its dives, its head has grown tough and as hard as tempered steel.

Name: shelgon
Summary: Shelgon is a Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Bagon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Shelgon's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Dragon Pulse and it has a Max CP of 2,031. Shelgon evolves into Salamence.
About: Inside Shelgon's armor-like shell, cells are in the midst of transformation to create an entirely new body. This Pokémon's shell is extremely heavy, making its movements sluggish.

Name: salamence
Summary: Salamence is a Dragon & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Shelgon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy, Dragon and Rock moves. Salamence's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Draco Meteor and it has a Max CP of 3,749.
About: Salamence came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this Pokémon's cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.

Name: beldum
Summary: Beldum is a Steel & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Ground and Ghost moves. Beldum's strongest moveset is Take Down & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 976. Beldum evolves into Metang.
About: Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic force courses throughout Beldum's body. This Pokémon communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of magnetism.

Name: metang
Summary: Metang is a Steel & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Beldum. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Ground and Ghost moves. Metang's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 1,721. Metang evolves into Metagross.
About: When two Beldum fuse together, Metang is formed. The brains of the Beldum are joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically, this Pokémon generates strong psychokinetic power.

Name: metagross
Summary: Metagross is a Steel & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Metang. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Ground and Ghost moves. Metagross's strongest moveset is Bullet Punch & Meteor Mash and it has a Max CP of 3,791.
About: Metagross has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This Pokémon can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.

Name: regirock
Summary: Regirock is an unobtainable legendary Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Regirock's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 3,122.
About: Regirock was sealed away by people long ago. If this Pokémon's body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.

Name: regice
Summary: Regice is a legendary Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Regice's strongest moveset is Lock-On & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 3,122.
About: Regice's body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can't be melted, even by fire. This Pokémon controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: registeel
Summary: Registeel is a legendary Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Ground and Fighting moves. Registeel's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,447.
About: Registeel has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this Pokémon eats.

Name: latias
Summary: Latias is a legendary Dragon & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Ghost, Dark, Dragon, Ice and Bug moves. Latias's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Outrage and it has a Max CP of 3,510.
About: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.

Name: latios
Summary: Latios is a legendary Dragon & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Ghost, Dark, Dragon, Ice and Bug moves. Latios's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 3,812.
About: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.

Name: kyogre
Summary: Kyogre is a legendary Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Kyogre's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 4,115.
About: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

Name: groudon
Summary: Groudon is a legendary Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Groudon's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 4,115.
About: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

Name: rayquaza
Summary: Rayquaza is a legendary Dragon & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy, Dragon and Rock moves. Rayquaza's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Outrage and it has a Max CP of 3,835.
About: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

Name: jirachi
Summary: Jirachi is an unobtainable mythical Steel & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Ground and Ghost moves. Jirachi's strongest moveset is Confusion & Doom Desire and it has a Max CP of 3,265.
About: A legend states that Jirachi will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this Pokémon senses danger, it will fight without awakening.

Name: deoxys
Summary: Deoxys (Normal) is a mythical Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Deoxys's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,160.
About: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokémon's chest appears to be its brain.

Name: magnezone
Summary: Magnezone is an Electric & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Magneton. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fire and Fighting moves. Magnezone's strongest moveset is Spark & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 3,205.
About: There are still people who believe that this Pokémon came from outer space. It emanates a powerful magnetic field.

Name: lickilicky
Summary: Lickilicky is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Lickitung. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Lickilicky's strongest moveset is Lick & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,467.
About: It uses its tongue much more skillfully than its hands or its feet. It can deftly pick up a single small bean with its tongue.

Name: rhyperior
Summary: Rhyperior is a Ground & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Rhydon. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Rhyperior's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Rock Wrecker and it has a Max CP of 3,733.
About: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

Name: happiny
Summary: Happiny is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Happiny's strongest moveset is Pound & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 371. Happiny evolves into Chansey.
About: When it sees something round and white, Happiny puts it into the pouch on its stomach. It sometimes becomes overloaded and can't move.

Name: tangrowth
Summary: Tangrowth is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Tangela. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Tangrowth's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 3,030.
About: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.

Name: mime jr.
Summary: Mime Jr. is a Psychic & Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Poison, Ghost and Steel moves. Mime Jr.'s strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 1,095. Mime Jr. evolves into Mr. Mime.
About: When this gifted mimic surprises an opponent, Mime Jr. feels so happy that it ends up forgetting it was imitating something.

Name: electivire
Summary: Electivire is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Electabuzz. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Electivire's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 3,079.
About: A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.

Name: magmortar
Summary: Magmortar is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Magmar. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Magmortar's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 3,132.
About: Magmortar takes down its enemies by shooting fireballs, which burn them to a blackened crisp. It avoids this method when hunting prey.

Name: leafeon
