Summary: Leafeon is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Leafeon's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,944.
About: It gets its nutrition from photosynthesis. It lives a quiet life deep in forests where clean rivers flow.

Name: glaceon
Summary: Glaceon is an Ice Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Glaceon's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 3,126.
About: It can instantaneously freeze any moisture that's around it, creating ice pellets to shoot at its prey.

Name: porygon-z
Summary: Porygon-Z is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Porygon2. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Porygon-Z's strongest moveset is Lock-On & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,266.
About: A faulty update was added to its programming. Its behavior is noticeably strange, so the experiment may have been a failure.

Name: munchlax
Summary: Munchlax is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Munchlax's strongest moveset is Tackle & Body Slam and it has a Max CP of 1,892. Munchlax evolves into Snorlax.
About: Anything that looks edible, Munchlax will go on and swallow whole. Its stomach is tough enough to handle it even if the food has gone rotten.

Name: togekiss
Summary: Togekiss is a Fairy & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Togetic. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ice, Poison, Rock and Electric moves. Togekiss's strongest moveset is Charm & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 3,332.
About: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

Name: bonsly
Summary: Bonsly is a Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Bonsly's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 1,302. Bonsly evolves into Sudowoodo.
About: If its body gets too damp, it will die. So, in a process reminiscent of sweating, its eyes expel moisture.

Name: ambipom
Summary: Ambipom is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Aipom. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Ambipom's strongest moveset is Scratch & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,418.
About: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that's proof it really likes you.

Name: yanmega
Summary: Yanmega is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Yanma. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Yanmega's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 2,946.
About: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

Name: honchkrow
Summary: Honchkrow is a Dark & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Murkrow. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Ice, Electric and Rock moves. Honchkrow's strongest moveset is Snarl & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 2,711.
About: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.

Name: mismagius
Summary: Mismagius is a Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Misdreavus. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Mismagius's strongest moveset is Hex & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,615.
About: Its muttered curses can cause awful headaches or terrifying visions that torment others.

Name: gliscor
Summary: Gliscor is a Ground & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Gligar. It is vulnerable to Ice and Water moves. Gliscor's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,692.
About: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

Name: weavile
Summary: Weavile is a Dark & Ice Pokémon which evolves from Sneasel. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Fairy, Bug, Steel, Fire and Rock moves. Weavile's strongest moveset is Snarl & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 3,005.
About: Thanks to its increased intelligence, scrapping over food is a thing of the past. A scratch from its claws will give you a case of frostbite!

Name: mamoswine
Summary: Mamoswine is an Ice & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Piloswine. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Grass, Water and Steel moves. Mamoswine's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 3,328.
About: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

Name: mantyke
Summary: Mantyke is a Water & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Mantyke's strongest moveset is Bubble & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 1,248. Mantyke evolves into Mantine.
About: Mantyke are friendly toward people and will approach boats closely. The patterns on their backs differ depending on their habitat.

Name: gallade
Summary: Gallade is a Psychic & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Kirlia. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Ghost moves. Gallade's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 3,093.
About: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

Name: probopass
Summary: Probopass is a Rock & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Nosepass. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting and Water moves. Probopass's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 2,080.
About: It uses three small units to catch prey and battle enemies. The main body mostly just gives orders.

Name: budew
Summary: Budew is a Grass & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Budew's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 856. Budew evolves into Roselia.
About: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

Name: roserade
Summary: Roserade is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Roselia. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Roserade's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,971.
About: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

Name: dusknoir
Summary: Dusknoir is a Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Dusclops. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Dusknoir's strongest moveset is Hex & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,388.
About: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

Name: chingling
Summary: Chingling is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Chingling's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,005. Chingling evolves into Chimecho.
About: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

Name: froslass
Summary: Froslass is an Ice & Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Snorunt. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Rock, Ghost and Steel moves. Froslass's strongest moveset is Hex & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,040.
About: It's said that on nights of terrible blizzards, it comes down to human settlements. If you hear it knocking at your door, do not open it!

Name: turtwig
Summary: Turtwig is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Turtwig's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Seed Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,187. Turtwig evolves into Grotle.
About: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

Name: grotle
Summary: Grotle is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Turtwig. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Grotle's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,890. Grotle evolves into Torterra.
About: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

Name: torterra
Summary: Torterra is a Grass & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Grotle. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fire, Flying and Bug moves. Torterra's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Frenzy Plant and it has a Max CP of 2,934.
About: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

Name: chimchar
Summary: Chimchar is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Chimchar's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 957. Chimchar evolves into Monferno.
About: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

Name: monferno
Summary: Monferno is a Fire & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Chimchar. It is vulnerable to Flying, Ground, Psychic and Water moves. Monferno's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,574. Monferno evolves into Infernape.
About: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

Name: infernape
Summary: Infernape is a Fire & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Monferno. It is vulnerable to Flying, Ground, Psychic and Water moves. Infernape's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Blast Burn and it has a Max CP of 2,683.
About: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

Name: piplup
Summary: Piplup is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Piplup's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,075. Piplup evolves into Prinplup.
About: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

Name: prinplup
Summary: Prinplup is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Piplup. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Prinplup's strongest moveset is Bubble & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 1,701. Prinplup evolves into Empoleon.
About: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

Name: empoleon
Summary: Empoleon is a Water & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Prinplup. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Ground and Electric moves. Empoleon's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Hydro Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,900.
About: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

Name: starly
Summary: Starly is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Starly's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Brave Bird and it has a Max CP of 719. Starly evolves into Staravia.
About: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

Name: staravia
Summary: Staravia is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Starly. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Staravia's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Brave Bird and it has a Max CP of 1,299. Staravia evolves into Staraptor.
About: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

Name: staraptor
Summary: Staraptor is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Staravia. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Staraptor's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Brave Bird and it has a Max CP of 2,825.
About: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

Name: bidoof
Summary: Bidoof is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Bidoof's strongest moveset is Tackle & Hyper Fang and it has a Max CP of 721. Bidoof evolves into Bibarel.
About: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

Name: bibarel
Summary: Bibarel is a Normal & Water Pokémon which evolves from Bidoof. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Electric and Grass moves. Bibarel's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,823.
About: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

Name: kricketot
Summary: Kricketot is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Kricketot's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 401. Kricketot evolves into Kricketune.
About: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

Name: kricketune
Summary: Kricketune is a Bug Pokémon which evolves from Kricketot. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Kricketune's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,653.
About: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

Name: shinx
Summary: Shinx is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Shinx's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 876. Shinx evolves into Luxio.
About: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

Name: luxio
Summary: Luxio is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Shinx. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Luxio's strongest moveset is Spark & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 1,486. Luxio evolves into Luxray.
About: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

Name: luxray
Summary: Luxray is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Luxio. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Luxray's strongest moveset is Snarl & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 2,888.
About: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

Name: cranidos
Summary: Cranidos is a Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Cranidos's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Ancient Power and it has a Max CP of 1,820. Cranidos evolves into Rampardos.
About: Its hard skull is its distinguishing feature. It snapped trees by headbutting them, and then it fed on their ripe berries.

Name: rampardos
Summary: Rampardos is a Rock Pokémon which evolves from Cranidos. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Rampardos's strongest moveset is Smack Down & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 3,298.
About: This ancient Pokémon used headbutts skillfully. Its brain was really small, so some theories suggest that its stupidity led to its extinction.

Name: shieldon
Summary: Shieldon is a Rock & Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting and Water moves. Shieldon's strongest moveset is Iron Tail & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 890. Shieldon evolves into Bastiodon.
About: Although its fossils can be found in layers of primeval rock, nothing but its face has ever been discovered.

Name: bastiodon
Summary: Bastiodon is a Rock & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Shieldon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting and Water moves. Bastiodon's strongest moveset is Iron Tail & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 1,539.
About: This Pokémon is from roughly 100 million years ago. Its terrifyingly tough face is harder than steel.

Name: burmy
Summary: Burmy (Plant) is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Burmy's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 488. Burmy (Plant) evolves into Wormadam (Plant).
About: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

Name: wormadam
Summary: Wormadam (Plant) is a Bug & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Burmy. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Rock, Bug and Ice moves. Wormadam's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,773.
About: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

Name: burmy
Summary: Burmy (Plant) is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Burmy's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 488. Burmy (Plant) evolves into Wormadam (Plant).
About: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

Name: wormadam
Summary: Wormadam (Plant) is a Bug & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Burmy. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Rock, Bug and Ice moves. Wormadam's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,773.
About: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

Name: combee
Summary: Combee is a Bug & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Combee's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 494. Combee evolves into Vespiquen.
About: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

Name: vespiquen
Summary: Vespiquen is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Combee. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Vespiquen's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 2,005.
About: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

Name: pachirisu
Summary: Pachirisu is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Pachirisu's strongest moveset is Volt Switch & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,213.
About: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

Name: buizel
Summary: Buizel is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Buizel's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,054. Buizel evolves into Floatzel.
About: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

Name: floatzel
Summary: Floatzel is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Buizel. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Floatzel's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,443.
About: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

Name: cherubi
Summary: Cherubi is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Cherubi's strongest moveset is Bullet Seed & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 950. Cherubi evolves into Cherrim (Overcast), Cherrim (Sunny).
About: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

Name: cherrim
Summary: Cherrim (Overcast) is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Cherubi. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Cherrim's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,048.
About: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.

Name: shellos
Summary: Shellos (West Sea) is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Shellos's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,136. Shellos (West Sea) evolves into Gastrodon (West Sea).
About: When it senses danger, a purple liquid oozes out of it. The liquid is thought to be something like greasy sweat.

Name: gastrodon
Summary: Gastrodon (West Sea) is a Water & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Shellos. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Gastrodon's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,324.
About: Their shape and color change, depending on their environment and diet. There are many of them at beaches where the waves are calm.

Name: drifloon
Summary: Drifloon is a Ghost & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ice, Rock, Ghost and Electric moves. Drifloon's strongest moveset is Hex & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,197. Drifloon evolves into Drifblim.
About: Wandering souls gathered together to form this Pokémon. When trying to make friends with children, Drifloon grabs them by the hand.

Name: drifblim
Summary: Drifblim is a Ghost & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Drifloon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ice, Rock, Ghost and Electric moves. Drifblim's strongest moveset is Hex & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,382.
About: The raw material for the gas inside its body is souls. When its body starts to deflate, it's thought to carry away people and Pokémon.

Name: buneary
Summary: Buneary is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Buneary's strongest moveset is Pound & Fire Punch and it has a Max CP of 1,258. Buneary evolves into Lopunny.
About: The reason it keeps one ear rolled up is so it can launch a swift counterattack if it's attacked by an enemy.

Name: lopunny
Summary: Lopunny is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Buneary. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Lopunny's strongest moveset is Pound & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,059.
About: It's notably wary and has a dislike of fighting, but at the same time, it can deliver powerful kicks with its lithe legs.

Name: glameow
Summary: Glameow is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Glameow's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 934. Glameow evolves into Purugly.
About: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

Name: purugly
Summary: Purugly is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Glameow. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Purugly's strongest moveset is Scratch & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,953.
About: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

Name: stunky
Summary: Stunky is a Poison & Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Stunky's strongest moveset is Bite & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,151. Stunky evolves into Skuntank.
About: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

Name: skuntank
Summary: Skuntank is a Poison & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Stunky. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Skuntank's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 2,358.
About: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

Name: bronzor
Summary: Bronzor is a Steel & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Ground and Ghost moves. Bronzor's strongest moveset is Confusion & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 603. Bronzor evolves into Bronzong.
About: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

Name: bronzong
Summary: Bronzong is a Steel & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Bronzor. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Ground and Ghost moves. Bronzong's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,239.
About: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.

Name: chatot
Summary: Chatot is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Chatot's strongest moveset is Peck & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 1,791.
About: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

Name: spiritomb
Summary: Spiritomb is a Ghost & Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy moves. Spiritomb's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,072.
About: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

Name: gible
Summary: Gible is a Dragon & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy and Dragon moves. Gible's strongest moveset is Mud Shot & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,112. Gible evolves into Gabite.
About: Its original home is an area much hotter than Alola. If you're planning to live with one, your heating bill will soar.

Name: gabite
Summary: Gabite is a Dragon & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Gible. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy and Dragon moves. Gabite's strongest moveset is Mud Shot & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,874. Gabite evolves into Garchomp.
About: It sheds its skin and gradually grows larger. Its scales can be ground into a powder and used as raw materials for traditional medicine.

Name: garchomp
Summary: Garchomp is a Dragon & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Gabite. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy and Dragon moves. Garchomp's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Outrage and it has a Max CP of 3,962.
About: Its fine scales don't just reduce wind resistance—their sharp edges also cause injury to any opponent who attacks it.

Name: riolu
Summary: Riolu is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Riolu's strongest moveset is Counter & Cross Chop and it has a Max CP of 993. Riolu evolves into Lucario.
About: It uses waves called auras to communicate with others of its kind. It doesn't make any noise during this time, so its enemies can't detect it.

Name: lucario
Summary: Lucario is a Fighting & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Riolu. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting and Ground moves. Lucario's strongest moveset is Counter & Aura Sphere and it has a Max CP of 2,703.

About: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: darmanitan
Summary: Darmanitan (Standard) is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Darumaka. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Darmanitan's strongest moveset is Fire Fang & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 3,105.
About: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

Name: maractus
Summary: Maractus is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Maractus's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,274.
About: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

Name: dwebble
Summary: Dwebble is a Bug & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Rock and Steel moves. Dwebble's strongest moveset is Smack Down & X-Scissor and it has a Max CP of 1,224. Dwebble evolves into Crustle.
About: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

Name: crustle
Summary: Crustle is a Bug & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Dwebble. It is vulnerable to Water, Rock and Steel moves. Crustle's strongest moveset is Smack Down & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 2,542.
About: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

Name: scraggy
Summary: Scraggy is a Dark & Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Flying moves. Scraggy's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 1,372. Scraggy evolves into Scrafty.
About: It stretches its saggy skin up to its neck to protect itself. The saggier their skin, the more respect they garner.

Name: scrafty
Summary: Scrafty is a Dark & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Scraggy. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Flying moves. Scrafty's strongest moveset is Counter & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 2,283.
About: It taunts its opponents by spitting. It has a certain territory that it never leaves its whole life long.

Name: sigilyph
Summary: Sigilyph is a Psychic & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ice, Rock, Electric and Ghost moves. Sigilyph's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Psybeam and it has a Max CP of 2,550.
About: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.

Name: yamask
Summary: Yamask is a Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Yamask's strongest moveset is Astonish & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 982. Yamask evolves into Cofagrigus.
About: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

Name: cofagrigus
Summary: Cofagrigus is a Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Yamask. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Cofagrigus's strongest moveset is Astonish & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,273.
About: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

Name: tirtouga
Summary: Tirtouga is a Water & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Tirtouga's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Surf and it has a Max CP of 1,488. Tirtouga evolves into Carracosta.
About: Its hunting grounds encompassed a broad area, from the land to more than half a mile deep in the ocean.

Name: carracosta
Summary: Carracosta is a Water & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Tirtouga. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Carracosta's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Surf and it has a Max CP of 2,621.
About: Carracosta eats every last bit of the prey it catches, even the shells and bones, to further strengthen its sturdy shell.

Name: archen
Summary: Archen is a Rock & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Steel, Water and Electric moves. Archen's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Ancient Power and it has a Max CP of 1,842. Archen evolves into Archeops.
About: Restored from a fossil, this ancient bird Pokémon has wings but can't yet fly.

Name: archeops
Summary: Archeops is a Rock & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Archen. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Steel, Water and Electric moves. Archeops's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Ancient Power and it has a Max CP of 3,331.
About: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, the muscles it uses to flap its wings are still weak, so it needs a long runway in order to take off.

Name: trubbish
Summary: Trubbish is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Trubbish's strongest moveset is Acid & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 1,000. Trubbish evolves into Garbodor.
About: If a young Pokémon or child breathes in the toxic gas that Trubbish belches out, it could be a life-threatening situation.

Name: garbodor
Summary: Garbodor is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Trubbish. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Garbodor's strongest moveset is Acid & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 2,345.
About: Some say the reason Garbodor in Alola are a little stronger than their counterparts elsewhere is the presence of Muk, their natural enemy.

Name: zorua
Summary: Zorua is a Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Zorua's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 1,175. Zorua evolves into Zoroark.
About: If a normally talkative child suddenly stops talking, it may have been replaced by Zorua.

Name: zoroark
Summary: Zoroark is a Dark Pokémon which evolves from Zorua. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Zoroark's strongest moveset is Snarl & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 2,571.
About: If it thinks humans are going to discover its den, Zoroark shows them visions that make them wander around in the woods.

Name: minccino
Summary: Minccino is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Minccino's strongest moveset is Pound & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 872. Minccino evolves into Cinccino.
About: When its tail has gotten dirty from self-cleaning or from cleaning its nest, Minccino spends a whole day washing its tail in clean spring water.

Name: cinccino
Summary: Cinccino is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Minccino. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Cinccino's strongest moveset is Pound & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,242.
About: The oil that seeps from its body is really smooth. For people troubled by bad skin, this oil is an effective treatment.

Name: gothita
Summary: Gothita is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Gothita's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 951. Gothita evolves into Gothorita.
About: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

Name: gothorita
Summary: Gothorita is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Gothita. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Gothorita's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 1,604. Gothorita evolves into Gothitelle.
About: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

Name: gothitelle
Summary: Gothitelle is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Gothorita. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Gothitelle's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,419.
About: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.

Name: solosis
Summary: Solosis is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Solosis's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Psyshock and it has a Max CP of 1,367. Solosis evolves into Duosion.
About: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

Name: duosion
Summary: Duosion is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Solosis. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Duosion's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Psyshock and it has a Max CP of 2,018. Duosion evolves into Reuniclus.
About: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

Name: reuniclus
Summary: Reuniclus is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Duosion. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Reuniclus's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Future Sight and it has a Max CP of 2,927.
About: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

Name: ducklett
Summary: Ducklett is a Water & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Ducklett's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Brave Bird and it has a Max CP of 856. Ducklett evolves into Swanna.
About: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

Name: swanna
Summary: Swanna is a Water & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Ducklett. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Swanna's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hurricane and it has a Max CP of 2,088.
About: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

Name: vanillite
Summary: Vanillite is an Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Vanillite's strongest moveset is Powder Snow & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,033. Vanillite evolves into Vanillish.
About: When the morning sun hit an icicle, it wished not to melt, and thus Vanillite was born. At night, it buries itself in snow to sleep.

Name: vanillish
Summary: Vanillish is an Ice Pokémon which evolves from Vanillite. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Vanillish's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,591. Vanillish evolves into Vanilluxe.
About: This hearty Pokémon survived the Ice Age. It's incredibly popular in very hot regions.

Name: vanilluxe
Summary: Vanilluxe is an Ice Pokémon which evolves from Vanillish. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Vanilluxe's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 2,822.
About: Vanilluxe is born when two Vanillish, half-melted by the day's light, stick to each other and freeze together in the cold return of night.

Name: deerling
Summary: Deerling (Spring) is a Normal & Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Deerling's strongest moveset is Tackle & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 1,135. Deerling (Spring) evolves into Sawsbuck (Spring).
About: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

Name: sawsbuck
Summary: Sawsbuck (Spring) is a Normal & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Deerling. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Sawsbuck's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,416.
About: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

Name: emolga
Summary: Emolga is an Electric & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice and Rock moves. Emolga's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,633.
About: As it flies, it scatters electricity around, so bird Pokémon keep their distance. That's why Emolga can keep all its food to itself.

Name: karrablast
Summary: Karrablast is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Karrablast's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & X-Scissor and it has a Max CP of 1,182. Karrablast evolves into Escavalier.
About: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

Name: escavalier
Summary: Escavalier is a Bug & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Karrablast. It is vulnerable to Fire moves. Escavalier's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Megahorn and it has a Max CP of 2,889.
About: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

Name: foongus
Summary: Foongus is a Grass & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Foongus's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 979. Foongus evolves into Amoonguss.
About: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball, then releases poison spores.

Name: amoonguss
Summary: Amoonguss is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Foongus. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Amoonguss's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 2,140.
About: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

Name: frillish
Summary: Frillish is a Water & Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Dark, Ghost and Electric moves. Frillish's strongest moveset is Bubble & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,257. Frillish evolves into Jellicent.
About: Using the invisible poison spikes on its veillike arms and legs, it paralyzes its enemies and causes them to drown.

Name: jellicent
Summary: Jellicent is a Water & Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Frillish. It is vulnerable to Grass, Dark, Ghost and Electric moves. Jellicent's strongest moveset is Bubble & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,338.
About: Fishermen are terrified of Jellicent. It's rumored to drag them into the sea and steal their lives away.

Name: alomomola
Summary: Alomomola is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Alomomola's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,169.
About: The reason it helps Pokémon in a weakened condition is that any Pokémon coming after them may also attack Alomomola.

Name: joltik
Summary: Joltik is a Bug & Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire and Rock moves. Joltik's strongest moveset is Charge Beam & Discharge and it has a Max CP of 1,023. Joltik evolves into Galvantula.
About: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

Name: galvantula
Summary: Galvantula is a Bug & Electric Pokémon which evolves from Joltik. It is vulnerable to Fire and Rock moves. Galvantula's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Discharge and it has a Max CP of 2,206.
About: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

Name: ferroseed
Summary: Ferroseed is a Grass & Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire and Fighting moves. Ferroseed's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Iron Head and it has a Max CP of 941. Ferroseed evolves into Ferrothorn.
About: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

Name: ferrothorn
Summary: Ferrothorn is a Grass & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Ferroseed. It is vulnerable to Fire and Fighting moves. Ferrothorn's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 2,321.
About: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

Name: klink
Summary: Klink is a Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Ground and Fighting moves. Klink's strongest moveset is Volt Switch & Zap Cannon and it has a Max CP of 956. Klink evolves into Klang.
About: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

Name: klang
Summary: Klang is a Steel Pokémon which evolves from Klink. It is vulnerable to Fire, Ground and Fighting moves. Klang's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,847. Klang evolves into Klinklang.
About: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.

Name: klinklang
Summary: Klinklang is a Steel Pokémon which evolves from Klang. It is vulnerable to Fire, Ground and Fighting moves. Klinklang's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,637.
About: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

Name: tynamo
Summary: Tynamo is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Tynamo's strongest moveset is Spark & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 811. Tynamo evolves into Eelektrik.
About: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

Name: eelektrik
Summary: Eelektrik is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Tynamo. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Eelektrik's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,715. Eelektrik evolves into Eelektross.
About: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

Name: eelektross
Summary: Eelektross is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Eelektrik. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Eelektross's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 2,732.
About: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

Name: elgyem
Summary: Elgyem is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Elgyem's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 1,385. Elgyem evolves into Beheeyem.
About: This Pokémon is shrouded in mystery. It's said to have appeared from a UFO that fell from the sky about 50 years ago.

Name: beheeyem
Summary: Beheeyem is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Elgyem. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Beheeyem's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,753.
About: It has strong psychic powers. Using its fingers that flash three different colors, it controls its opponents and rewrites their memories.

Name: litwick
Summary: Litwick is a Ghost & Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Rock, Ghost and Water moves. Litwick's strongest moveset is Ember & Flame Burst and it has a Max CP of 1,006. Litwick evolves into Lampent.
About: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

Name: lampent
Summary: Lampent is a Ghost & Fire Pokémon which evolves from Litwick. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Rock, Ghost and Water moves. Lampent's strongest moveset is Ember & Flame Burst and it has a Max CP of 1,708. Lampent evolves into Chandelure.
About: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

Name: chandelure
Summary: Chandelure is a Ghost & Fire Pokémon which evolves from Lampent. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Rock, Ghost and Water moves. Chandelure's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 3,268.
About: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

Name: axew
Summary: Axew is a Dragon Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Axew's strongest moveset is Iron Tail & Dragon Claw and it has a Max CP of 1,368. Axew evolves into Fraxure.
About: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

Name: fraxure
Summary: Fraxure is a Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Axew. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Fraxure's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Dragon Claw and it has a Max CP of 2,234. Fraxure evolves into Haxorus.
About: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

Name: haxorus
Summary: Haxorus is a Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Fraxure. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Haxorus's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Dragon Claw and it has a Max CP of 3,593.
About: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

Name: cubchoo
Summary: Cubchoo is an Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Cubchoo's strongest moveset is Charm & Ice Punch and it has a Max CP of 1,069. Cubchoo evolves into Beartic.
About: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

Name: beartic
Summary: Beartic is an Ice Pokémon which evolves from Cubchoo. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Beartic's strongest moveset is Charm & Ice Punch and it has a Max CP of 3,042.
About: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

Name: cryogonal
Summary: Cryogonal is an Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Cryogonal's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,798.
About: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: shelmet
Summary: Shelmet is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Shelmet's strongest moveset is Infestation & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 834. Shelmet evolves into Accelgor.
About: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

Name: accelgor
Summary: Accelgor is a Bug Pokémon which evolves from Shelmet. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Accelgor's strongest moveset is Infestation & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 2,441.
About: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

Name: stunfisk
Summary: Stunfisk is a Ground & Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Ground, Ice and Grass moves. Stunfisk's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Discharge and it has a Max CP of 2,162.
About: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

Name: mienfoo
Summary: Mienfoo is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Mienfoo's strongest moveset is Low Kick & Focus Blast and it has a Max CP of 1,389. Mienfoo evolves into Mienshao.
About: They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.

Name: mienshao
Summary: Mienshao is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Mienfoo. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Mienshao's strongest moveset is Low Kick & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 2,710.
About: When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail, you're in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!

Name: druddigon
Summary: Druddigon is a Dragon Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Druddigon's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Dragon Claw and it has a Max CP of 2,732.
About: It infiltrates tunnels that Pokémon like Diglett and Dugtrio have dug and quietly waits for prey to pass through.

Name: golett
Summary: Golett is a Ground & Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Dark, Ice, Grass and Ghost moves. Golett's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Shadow Punch and it has a Max CP of 1,189. Golett evolves into Golurk.
About: Although ancient people apparently built it by working with clay, the source of its energy is unclear.

Name: golurk
Summary: Golurk is a Ground & Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Golett. It is vulnerable to Water, Dark, Ice, Grass and Ghost moves. Golurk's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earth Power and it has a Max CP of 2,854.
About: When the seal on its chest is removed, it rages indiscriminately, turning the whole town around it into a mountain of rubble.

Name: pawniard
Summary: Pawniard is a Dark & Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Fire and Ground moves. Pawniard's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Iron Head and it has a Max CP of 1,433. Pawniard evolves into Bisharp.
About: It follows Bisharp's orders to a tee when it attacks enemies. After slashing an opponent, Pawniard clangs both of its blades together.

Name: bisharp
Summary: Bisharp is a Dark & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Pawniard. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Fire and Ground moves. Bisharp's strongest moveset is Snarl & Iron Head and it has a Max CP of 2,844.
About: It leads a group of Pawniard. Bisharp doesn't even change its expression when it deals the finishing blow to an opponent.

Name: bouffalant
Summary: Bouffalant is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Bouffalant's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Skull Bash and it has a Max CP of 2,797.
About: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

Name: rufflet
Summary: Rufflet is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Rufflet's strongest moveset is Peck & Brave Bird and it has a Max CP of 1,491. Rufflet evolves into Braviary.
About: Known as a natural-born warrior, soon after its hatching, it will challenge its parent to a fight in order to gain their acceptance.

Name: braviary
Summary: Braviary is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Rufflet. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Braviary's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Brave Bird and it has a Max CP of 3,088.
About: Known as “the hero of the skies, this Pokémon is so proud and so brave that it will never retreat, even when it's injured.

Name: vullaby
Summary: Vullaby is a Dark & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Ice, Electric and Rock moves. Vullaby's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 1,271. Vullaby evolves into Mandibuzz.
About: Its healthy appetite leads to visible growth spurts. It often has to replace the bones it wears as its size increases.

Name: mandibuzz
Summary: Mandibuzz is a Dark & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Vullaby. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Ice, Electric and Rock moves. Mandibuzz's strongest moveset is Snarl & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 2,138.
About: It's always searching for food for Vullaby. When it finds a weak Pokémon, Mandibuzz swoops it right off to its nest.

Name: heatmor
Summary: Heatmor is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Heatmor's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 2,395.
About: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.

Name: durant
Summary: Durant is a Bug & Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire moves. Durant's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Iron Head and it has a Max CP of 2,659.
About: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

Name: deino
Summary: Deino is a Dark & Dragon Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Bug, Dragon, Ice and Fighting moves. Deino's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Dragon Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,062. Deino evolves into Zweilous.
About: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.

Name: zweilous
Summary: Zweilous is a Dark & Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Deino. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Bug, Dragon, Ice and Fighting moves. Zweilous's strongest moveset is Bite & Dragon Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,839. Zweilous evolves into Hydreigon.
About: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

Name: hydreigon
Summary: Hydreigon is a Dark & Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Zweilous. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Bug, Dragon, Ice and Fighting moves. Hydreigon's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Dragon Pulse and it has a Max CP of 3,625.
About: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!

Name: larvesta
Summary: Larvesta is a Bug & Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Water and Flying moves. Larvesta's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,496. Larvesta evolves into Volcarona.
About: It protects itself with flame. Long years ago, people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.

Name: volcarona
Summary: Volcarona is a Bug & Fire Pokémon which evolves from Larvesta. It is vulnerable to Rock, Water and Flying moves. Volcarona's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 3,632.
About: According to legends, it was hatched from a flaming cocoon to save people and Pokémon that were suffering from the cold.

Name: cobalion
Summary: Cobalion is a legendary Steel & Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting and Ground moves. Cobalion's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Sacred Sword and it has a Max CP of 3,022.
About: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

Name: terrakion
Summary: Terrakion is a legendary Rock & Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Psychic, Ground, Steel, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Terrakion's strongest moveset is Smack Down & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 3,698.
About: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

Name: virizion
Summary: Virizion is a legendary Grass & Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Flying, Fairy, Psychic, Ice, Fire and Poison moves. Virizion's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Leaf Blade and it has a Max CP of 3,022.
About: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

Name: tornadus
Summary: Tornadus (Incarnate) is a legendary Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Tornadus's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 3,345.
About: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

Name: thundurus
Summary: Thundurus (Incarnate) is a legendary Electric & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice and Rock moves. Thundurus's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunder and it has a Max CP of 3,345.
About: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

Name: reshiram
Summary: Reshiram is a legendary Dragon & Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dragon, Ground and Rock moves. Reshiram's strongest moveset is Fire Fang & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 4,038.
About: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

Name: zekrom
Summary: Zekrom is a legendary Dragon & Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon, Ground and Ice moves. Zekrom's strongest moveset is Charge Beam & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 4,038.
About: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

Name: landorus
Summary: Landorus (Incarnate) is a legendary Ground & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice and Water moves. Landorus's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Earth Power and it has a Max CP of 3,588.
About: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

Name: kyurem
Summary: Kyurem is a legendary Dragon & Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Steel, Dragon, Rock and Fighting moves. Kyurem's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Draco Meteor and it has a Max CP of 3,575.
About: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

Name: keldeo
Summary: Keldeo (Ordinary) is a mythical Water & Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying, Psychic, Electric and Grass moves. Keldeo's strongest moveset is Low Kick & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 3,698.
About: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

Name: meloetta
Summary: Meloetta (Aria) is a mythical Normal & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug and Dark moves. Meloetta's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,972.
About: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

Name: genesect
Summary: Genesect is a mythical Bug & Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire moves. Genesect's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Magnet Bomb and it has a Max CP of 3,353.
About: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

Name: meltan
Summary: Meltan is a mythical Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Ground and Fighting moves. Meltan's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,068. Meltan evolves into Melmetal.
About: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

Name: melmetal
Summary: Melmetal is a mythical Steel Pokémon which evolves from Meltan. It is vulnerable to Fire, Ground and Fighting moves. Melmetal's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,599.
About: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.
